Script: MACE WiNDU: That could be a dangerous move ... the Jedi Council would have to take control of the Senate in order to secure a peaceful transition . . .
Dialogue: That could be a dangerous move ... the Jedi Council would have to take control of the Senate in order to secure a peaceful transition . . .

Script: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: . . . and replace the Congress with Senators who are not filled with greed and corruption.
Dialogue: . . . and replace the Congress with Senators who are not filled with greed and corruption.

Script: YODA: To a dark place this line of thought will carry us. Hmmmmm. . . . great care we must take.
Dialogue: To a dark place this line of thought will carry us. Hmmmmm. . . . great care we must take.

Script: ANAKIN: Chancellor we have just received a report from Master Kenobi. He has engaged General Grievous.
Dialogue: Chancellor we have just received a report from Master Kenobi. He has engaged General Grievous.

Script: PALPATINE: We can only hope that Master Kenobi is up to the challenge.
Dialogue: We can only hope that Master Kenobi is up to the challenge.

Script: ANAKIN: I should be there with him.
Dialogue: I should be there with him.

Script: PALPATINE: It is upsetting to me to see that the Council doesn't seem to fully appreciate your talents. Don't you wonder why they won't make you a Jedi Master?
Dialogue: It is upsetting to me to see that the Council doesn't seem to fully appreciate your talents. Don't you wonder why they won't make you a Jedi Master?

Script: ANAKIN: I wish I knew. More and more I get the feeling that I am being excluded from the Council. I know there are things about the Force that they are not telling me.
Dialogue: I wish I knew. More and more I get the feeling that I am being excluded from the Council. I know there are things about the Force that they are not telling me.

Script: PALPATINE: They don't trust you Anakin. They see your future. They know your power will be too strong to control. Anakin you must break through the fog of lies the Jedi have created around you. Let me help you to know the subtleties of the Force.
Dialogue: They don't trust you Anakin. They see your future. They know your power will be too strong to control. Anakin you must break through the fog of lies the Jedi have created around you. Let me help you to know the subtleties of the Force.

Script: ANAKIN: How do you know the ways of the Force?
Dialogue: How do you know the ways of the Force?

Script: PALPATINE: My mentor taught me everything about the Force . . . even the nature of the dark side.
Dialogue: My mentor taught me everything about the Force . . . even the nature of the dark side.

Script: ANAKIN: You know the dark side?!?
Dialogue: You know the dark side?!?

Script: PALPATINE: Anakin if one is to understand the great mystery one must study all its aspects not just the dogmatic narrow view of the Jedi. If you wish to become a complete and wise leader you must embrace a larger view of the Force. Be careful of the Jedi Anakin. (pausing) They fear you. In time they will destroy you. Let me train you.
Dialogue: Anakin if one is to understand the great mystery one must study all its aspects not just the dogmatic narrow view of the Jedi. If you wish to become a complete and wise leader you must embrace a larger view of the Force. Be careful of the Jedi Anakin.  They fear you. In time they will destroy you. Let me train you.

Script: ANAKIN: I won't be a pawn in your political game. The Jedi are my family.
Dialogue: I won't be a pawn in your political game. The Jedi are my family.

Script: PALPATINE: Only through me can you achieve a power greater than any Jedi. Learn to know the dark side of the Force Anakin and you will be able to save your wife from certain death.
Dialogue: Only through me can you achieve a power greater than any Jedi. Learn to know the dark side of the Force Anakin and you will be able to save your wife from certain death.

Script: ANAKIN: What did you say?
Dialogue: What did you say?

Script: PALPATINE: Use my knowledge I beg you . . .
Dialogue: Use my knowledge I beg you . . .

Script: ANAKIN: You're a Sith Lord!
Dialogue: You're a Sith Lord!

Script: PALPATINE: I know what has been troubling you . . . Listen to me. Don't continue to be a pawn of the Jedi Council! Ever since I've known you you've been searching for a life greater than that of an ordinary Jedi . . . a life of significance of conscience.
Dialogue: I know what has been troubling you . . . Listen to me. Don't continue to be a pawn of the Jedi Council! Ever since I've known you you've been searching for a life greater than that of an ordinary Jedi . . . a life of significance of conscience.

Script: ANAKIN: You're wrong!
Dialogue: You're wrong!

Script: PALPATINE: Are you going to kill me?
Dialogue: Are you going to kill me?

Script: ANAKIN: I would certainly like to.
Dialogue: I would certainly like to.

Script: PALPATINE: I know you would. I can feel your anger. It gives you focus makes you stronger.
Dialogue: I know you would. I can feel your anger. It gives you focus makes you stronger.

Script: ANAKIN: I am going to turn you over to the Jedi Council.
Dialogue: I am going to turn you over to the Jedi Council.

Script: PALPATINE: Of course you should. But you're not sure of their intentions are you? What if I am right and they are plotting to take over the Republic?
Dialogue: Of course you should. But you're not sure of their intentions are you? What if I am right and they are plotting to take over the Republic?

Script: ANAKIN: I will quickly discover the truth of all this.
Dialogue: I will quickly discover the truth of all this.

Script: PALPATINE: You have great wisdom Anakin. Know the power of the dark side. The power to save Padme.
Dialogue: You have great wisdom Anakin. Know the power of the dark side. The power to save Padme.

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) I am not going anywhere. You have time to decide my fate. Perhaps you'll reconsider and help me rule the galaxy for the good of all . . .
Dialogue: I am not going anywhere. You have time to decide my fate. Perhaps you'll reconsider and help me rule the galaxy for the good of all . . .

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Prepare to move out of orbit. I will be up in a few moments.
Dialogue: Prepare to move out of orbit. I will be up in a few moments.

Script: OBI-WAN: So uncivilized . . .
Dialogue: So uncivilized . . .

Script: ANAKIN: Master Windu I must talk to you.
Dialogue: Master Windu I must talk to you.

Script: MACE WiNDU: What is it Skywalker? We are in a hurry. We have just received word that Obi-Wan has destroyed General Grievous. We are on our way to make sure the Chancellor returns emergency powers back to the Senate.
Dialogue: What is it Skywalker? We are in a hurry. We have just received word that Obi-Wan has destroyed General Grievous. We are on our way to make sure the Chancellor returns emergency powers back to the Senate.

Script: ANAKIN: He won't give up his power. I've just learned a terrible truth. I think Chancellor Palpatine is a Sith Lord.
Dialogue: He won't give up his power. I've just learned a terrible truth. I think Chancellor Palpatine is a Sith Lord.

Script: MACE WINDU: A Sith Lord?
Dialogue: A Sith Lord?

Script: ANAKIN: Yes. The one we have been looking for.
Dialogue: Yes. The one we have been looking for.

Script: MACE WiNDU: How do you know this?
Dialogue: How do you know this?

Script: ANAKIN: He knows the ways of the Force. He has been trained to use the dark side.
Dialogue: He knows the ways of the Force. He has been trained to use the dark side.

Script: MACE WiNDU: Are you sure?
Dialogue: Are you sure?

Script: ANAKIN: Absolutely.
Dialogue: Absolutely.

Script: MACE WiNDU: Then our worst fears have been realized. We must move quickly if the Jedi Order is to survive.
Dialogue: Then our worst fears have been realized. We must move quickly if the Jedi Order is to survive.

Script: ANAKIN: Master the Chancellor is very powerful. You will need my help if you are going to arrest him.
Dialogue: Master the Chancellor is very powerful. You will need my help if you are going to arrest him.

Script: MACE WiNDU: For your own good stay out of this affair. I sense a great deal of confusion in you young Skywalker. There is much fear that clouds your judgment.
Dialogue: For your own good stay out of this affair. I sense a great deal of confusion in you young Skywalker. There is much fear that clouds your judgment.

Script: ANAKIN: I must go Master.
Dialogue: I must go Master.

Script: MACE WiNDU: No. If what you told me is true you will have gained my trust but for now remain here.
Dialogue: No. If what you told me is true you will have gained my trust but for now remain here.

Script: ANAKIN: Yes Master.
Dialogue: Yes Master.

Script: MACE WiNDU: Wait for us in the Council Chamber until we return.
Dialogue: Wait for us in the Council Chamber until we return.

Script: ANAKIN: Yes Master.
Dialogue: Yes Master.

Script: PALPATINE: (V.O.) You do know don't you if the Jedi destroy me any chance of saving her will be lost.
Dialogue: You do know don't you if the Jedi destroy me any chance of saving her will be lost.

Script: PADME: I truly deeply love you. Before I die. I want you to know.
Dialogue: I truly deeply love you. Before I die. I want you to know.

Script: C-3PO: My Lady are you. . . . Are you all right?
Dialogue: My Lady are you. . . . Are you all right?

Script: ANAKIN: I can't do this ... I can't let her die.
Dialogue: I can't do this ... I can't let her die.

Script: PALPATINE: Master Windu. I take it General Grievous has been destroyed then. I must say you're here sooner than expected.
Dialogue: Master Windu. I take it General Grievous has been destroyed then. I must say you're here sooner than expected.

Script: MACE WINDU: In the name of the Galactic Senate of the Republic you are under arrest Chancellor.
Dialogue: In the name of the Galactic Senate of the Republic you are under arrest Chancellor.

Script: PALPATINE: Are you threatening me Master Jedi?
Dialogue: Are you threatening me Master Jedi?

Script: MACE: The Senate will decide your fate.
Dialogue: The Senate will decide your fate.

Script: PALPATINE: (burst of anger) I am the Senate!
Dialogue: I am the Senate!

Script: MACE: Not yet!
Dialogue: Not yet!

Script: PALPATINE: It's treason then.
Dialogue: It's treason then.

Script: MACE WINDU: You are under arrest My Lord.
Dialogue: You are under arrest My Lord.

Script: PALPATINE: Anakin! I told you it would come to this. I was right. The Jedi are taking over.
Dialogue: Anakin! I told you it would come to this. I was right. The Jedi are taking over.

Script: MACE WlNDU: You old fool. The oppression of the Sith will never return. Your plot to regain control of the Republic is over . . . you have lost . . .
Dialogue: You old fool. The oppression of the Sith will never return. Your plot to regain control of the Republic is over . . . you have lost . . .

Script: PALPATINE: No! No! You will die!
Dialogue: No! No! You will die!

Script: PALPATINE: He is a traitor Anakin.
Dialogue: He is a traitor Anakin.

Script: MACE WlNDU: He's the traitor. Stop him!
Dialogue: He's the traitor. Stop him!

Script: PALPATINE: Come to your senses boy. The Jedi are in revolt. They will betray you just as they betrayed me.
Dialogue: Come to your senses boy. The Jedi are in revolt. They will betray you just as they betrayed me.

Script: MACE WlNDU: Aarrrrggghhhhh . . .
Dialogue: Aarrrrggghhhhh . . .

Script: PALPATINE: You are not one of them Anakin. Don't let him kill me.
Dialogue: You are not one of them Anakin. Don't let him kill me.

Script: MACE WlNDU: Aarrrrggghhhhh . . .
Dialogue: Aarrrrggghhhhh . . .

Script: PALPATINE: I am your pathway to power. I have the power to save the one you love. You must choose. You must stop him.
Dialogue: I am your pathway to power. I have the power to save the one you love. You must choose. You must stop him.

Script: MACE WlNDU: Don't listen to him Anakin.
Dialogue: Don't listen to him Anakin.

Script: PALPATINE: Help me! Don't let him kill me. I can't hold on any longer. Ahhhhhhh . . . ahhhhhhh . . . ahhhhhhh . . .
Dialogue: Help me! Don't let him kill me. I can't hold on any longer. Ahhhhhhh . . . ahhhhhhh . . . ahhhhhhh . . .

Script: PALPATINE: I can't ... I give up. Help me. I am weak ... I am too weak. Don't kill me. I give up. I'm dying. I can't hold on any longer.
Dialogue: I can't ... I give up. Help me. I am weak ... I am too weak. Don't kill me. I give up. I'm dying. I can't hold on any longer.

Script: MACE WlNDU: You Sith disease. I am going to end this once and for all.
Dialogue: You Sith disease. I am going to end this once and for all.

Script: ANAKIN: You can't kill him Master. He must stand trial.
Dialogue: You can't kill him Master. He must stand trial.

Script: MACE WlNDU: He has too much control of the Senate and the Courts. He is too dangerous to be kept alive.
Dialogue: He has too much control of the Senate and the Courts. He is too dangerous to be kept alive.

Script: PALPATINE: I'm too weak. Don't kill me. Please.
Dialogue: I'm too weak. Don't kill me. Please.

Script: ANAKIN: It is not the Jedi way . . .
Dialogue: It is not the Jedi way . . .

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) He must live . . .
Dialogue: He must live . . .

Script: PALPATINE: Please don't please don't . . .
Dialogue: Please don't please don't . . .

Script: ANAKIN: I need him . . .
Dialogue: I need him . . .

Script: PALPATINE: Please don't . . .
Dialogue: Please don't . . .

Script: ANAKIN: NO!!!
Dialogue: NO!!!

Script: PALPATINE: Power! Unlimited power!
Dialogue: Power! Unlimited power!

Script: ANAKIN: What have I done?
Dialogue: What have I done?

Script: PALPATINE: You are fulfilling your destin Anakin. Become my apprentice. Learn to use the dark side of the Force.
Dialogue: You are fulfilling your destin Anakin. Become my apprentice. Learn to use the dark side of the Force.

Script: ANAKIN: I will do whatever you ask.
Dialogue: I will do whatever you ask.

Script: PALPATINE: Good.
Dialogue: Good.

Script: ANAKIN: Just help me save Padme's life. I can't live without her. I won't let her die. I want the power to stop death.
Dialogue: Just help me save Padme's life. I can't live without her. I won't let her die. I want the power to stop death.

Script: PALPATINE: To cheat death is a power only one has achieved but if we work together I know we can discover the secret.
Dialogue: To cheat death is a power only one has achieved but if we work together I know we can discover the secret.

Script: ANAKIN: I pledge myself to your teachings. To the ways of the Sith.
Dialogue: I pledge myself to your teachings. To the ways of the Sith.

Script: PALPATINE: Good. Good. The Force is strong with you. A powerful Sith you will become. Henceforth you shall be known as Darth . . . Vader.
Dialogue: Good. Good. The Force is strong with you. A powerful Sith you will become. Henceforth you shall be known as Darth . . . Vader.

Script: ANAKIN: Thank you. my Master.
Dialogue: Thank you. my Master.

Script: PALPATINE: Rise Darth Vader.
Dialogue: Rise Darth Vader.

Script: PALPATINE: Because the Council did not trust you my young apprentice I believe you are the only Jedi with no knowledge of this plot. When the Jedi learn what has transpired here they will kill us along with all the Senators.
Dialogue: Because the Council did not trust you my young apprentice I believe you are the only Jedi with no knowledge of this plot. When the Jedi learn what has transpired here they will kill us along with all the Senators.

Script: ANAKIN: I agree. The Jedi's next move will be against the Senate.
Dialogue: I agree. The Jedi's next move will be against the Senate.

Script: PALPATINE: Every single Jedi including your friend Obi-Wan Kenobi is now an enemy of the Republic. You understand that don't you?
Dialogue: Every single Jedi including your friend Obi-Wan Kenobi is now an enemy of the Republic. You understand that don't you?

Script: ANAKIN: I understand Master.
Dialogue: I understand Master.

Script: PALPATINE: We must move quickly. The Jedi are relentless; if they are not all destroyed it will be civil war without end. First I want you to go to the Jedi Temple. We will catch them off balance. Do what must be done Lord Vader. Do not hesitate. Show no mercy. Only then will you be strong enough with the dark side to save Padme.
Dialogue: We must move quickly. The Jedi are relentless; if they are not all destroyed it will be civil war without end. First I want you to go to the Jedi Temple. We will catch them off balance. Do what must be done Lord Vader. Do not hesitate. Show no mercy. Only then will you be strong enough with the dark side to save Padme.

Script: ANAKIN: What about the other Jedi spread across the galaxy?
Dialogue: What about the other Jedi spread across the galaxy?

Script: PALPATINE: Their betrayal will be dealt with. After you have killed all the Jedi in the Temple go to the Mustafar system. Wipe out Viceroy Gunray and the other Separatist leaders. Once more the Sith will rule the galaxy and we shall have peace.
Dialogue: Their betrayal will be dealt with. After you have killed all the Jedi in the Temple go to the Mustafar system. Wipe out Viceroy Gunray and the other Separatist leaders. Once more the Sith will rule the galaxy and we shall have peace.

Script: OBI-WAN: Commander contact your troops. Tell them to move to the higher levels.
Dialogue: Commander contact your troops. Tell them to move to the higher levels.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: Very good sir.
Dialogue: Very good sir.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: (continuing) Oh by the way I think you'll be needing this.
Dialogue: Oh by the way I think you'll be needing this.

Script: OBI-WAN: Thank you Cody (smiling) Now let's get a move on. We've got a battle to win here.
Dialogue: Thank you Cody  Now let's get a move on. We've got a battle to win here.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: Yes sir!
Dialogue: Yes sir!

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Commander Cody the time has come. Execute Order Sixty-Six.
Dialogue: Commander Cody the time has come. Execute Order Sixty-Six.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: It will be done My Lord.
Dialogue: It will be done My Lord.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: Blast him!
Dialogue: Blast him!

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Commander 1138 . . .
Dialogue: Commander 1138 . . .

Script: CLONE COMMANDER BACARA: Yes sir.
Dialogue: Yes sir.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: The time has come. Execute Order Sixty-Six.
Dialogue: The time has come. Execute Order Sixty-Six.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER BACARA: It will be done My Lord.
Dialogue: It will be done My Lord.

Script: AAYLA: Steady. . . . steady . . .
Dialogue: Steady. . . . steady . . .

Script: AAYLA: (continuing) Bly do you think they're Droids?
Dialogue: Bly do you think they're Droids?

Script: BLY: No.
Dialogue: No.

Script: DARTH SIDIOUS: Execute Order Sixty-Six.
Dialogue: Execute Order Sixty-Six.

Script: CLONE PILOT: It will be done My Lord.
Dialogue: It will be done My Lord.

Script: PLO KOON: There they are. Land on the nearest platform.
Dialogue: There they are. Land on the nearest platform.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER GREE: Yes My Lord.
Dialogue: Yes My Lord.

Script: DABTH SIDIOUS: The time has come. Execute Order Sixty-Six.
Dialogue: The time has come. Execute Order Sixty-Six.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER GREE: It will be done My Lord.
Dialogue: It will be done My Lord.

Script: YOUNGLINGS: Master Skywalker there are too many of them. What are we going to do?
Dialogue: Master Skywalker there are too many of them. What are we going to do?

Script: C-3PO: The Chancellor's office indicated Master Anakin returned to the Jedi Temple. Don't worry My Lady. I am sure he will be all right.
Dialogue: The Chancellor's office indicated Master Anakin returned to the Jedi Temple. Don't worry My Lady. I am sure he will be all right.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: What's going on here?!?
Dialogue: What's going on here?!?

Script: CLONE SERGEANT: There's been a rebellion. Don't worry sir the situation is under control.
Dialogue: There's been a rebellion. Don't worry sir the situation is under control.

Script: CLONE SERGEANT: (continuing) I'm sorry sir. No one is allowed entry.
Dialogue: I'm sorry sir. No one is allowed entry.

Script: CLONE SERGEANT: (continuing) It's time for you to leave sir.
Dialogue: It's time for you to leave sir.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: And so it is.
Dialogue: And so it is.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER APPO: Get him! Shoot him!
Dialogue: Get him! Shoot him!

Script: AT-ST CLONE SERGEANT: Everyone out of there!
Dialogue: Everyone out of there!

Script: CREATURE: Wookiee good . . . eat Wookiee. (crazy little laugh)
Dialogue: Wookiee good . . . eat Wookiee.

Script: CLONE SERGEANT: Did you find something?
Dialogue: Did you find something?

Script: CREATURE: It's nothing nothing. (laughs)
Dialogue: It's nothing nothing.

Script: CLONE SERGEANT: It's nothing nothing. All these Wookiees are dead. Move to the east.
Dialogue: It's nothing nothing. All these Wookiees are dead. Move to the east.

Script: CLONE TROOPER: Yes sir.
Dialogue: Yes sir.

Script: CREATURE: Right you are Chewbacca. Faster that will be.
Dialogue: Right you are Chewbacca. Faster that will be.

Script: YODA: Stink this mud does. A moment to bathe give me.
Dialogue: Stink this mud does. A moment to bathe give me.

Script: YODA: (continuing) Not far are we from the emergency ship. Quickly . . .
Dialogue: Not far are we from the emergency ship. Quickly . . .

Script: YODA: Good-bye. Chewbacca and Tarfful miss you I will. Good friends you are. For your help much gratitude and respect I have.
Dialogue: Good-bye. Chewbacca and Tarfful miss you I will. Good friends you are. For your help much gratitude and respect I have.

Script: ROYAL GUARD: Identification . . .
Dialogue: Identification . . .

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Senator Bail Organa of Alderaan.
Dialogue: Senator Bail Organa of Alderaan.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Were you able to get hold of a Jedi homing beacon?
Dialogue: Were you able to get hold of a Jedi homing beacon?

Script: CAPTAIN ANTILLES: Yes sir. We've encountered no opposition. The clones are still a bit confused. It appears no one is in command.
Dialogue: Yes sir. We've encountered no opposition. The clones are still a bit confused. It appears no one is in command.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: That will change soon. Hopefully we will be able to intercept a few Jedi before they walk into this catastrophe.
Dialogue: That will change soon. Hopefully we will be able to intercept a few Jedi before they walk into this catastrophe.

Script: CLONE CAPTAIN: Did you find Kenobi?
Dialogue: Did you find Kenobi?

Script: CLONE TROOPER: No one could have survived that fall.
Dialogue: No one could have survived that fall.

Script: CLONE CAPTAIN: Start loading your men on the ship.
Dialogue: Start loading your men on the ship.

Script: CLONE TROOPER: Yes sir.
Dialogue: Yes sir.

Script: OBI-WAN: Emergency Code Nine Thirteen ... I have no contact on any frequency. Are there any Jedi out there? . . . anywhere . . .
Dialogue: Emergency Code Nine Thirteen ... I have no contact on any frequency. Are there any Jedi out there? . . . anywhere . . .

Script: BAIL: (hologram) . . . Kenobi . . .
Dialogue: . . . Kenobi . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) I've locked on. Repeat.
Dialogue: I've locked on. Repeat.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Master Kenobi??
Dialogue: Master Kenobi??

Script: OBI-WAN: Senator Organa! My Clone Troops turned on me ... I need help.
Dialogue: Senator Organa! My Clone Troops turned on me ... I need help.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: We have just rescued Master Yoda. It appears this ambush has happened everywhere. We're sending you our coordinates.
Dialogue: We have just rescued Master Yoda. It appears this ambush has happened everywhere. We're sending you our coordinates.

Script: C-3PO: My Lady there's a Jedi fighter docking on the veranda.
Dialogue: My Lady there's a Jedi fighter docking on the veranda.

Script: THREEPIO: Hush! Not so loud!
Dialogue: Hush! Not so loud!

Script: PADME: Are you all right? I heard there was an attack on the Jedi Temple . . . you can see the smoke from here.
Dialogue: Are you all right? I heard there was an attack on the Jedi Temple . . . you can see the smoke from here.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm fine. I'm fine. I came to see if you and the baby are safe.
Dialogue: I'm fine. I'm fine. I came to see if you and the baby are safe.

Script: PADME: Captain Typho's here we're safe. What's happening?
Dialogue: Captain Typho's here we're safe. What's happening?

Script: C-3PO: What is going on?
Dialogue: What is going on?

Script: C-3PO: (continuing) You can't be anymore confused than I am.
Dialogue: You can't be anymore confused than I am.

Script: ANAKIN: The situation is not good. The Jedi have tried to overthrow the Republic . . .
Dialogue: The situation is not good. The Jedi have tried to overthrow the Republic . . .

Script: PADME: I can't believe that!
Dialogue: I can't believe that!

Script: ANAKIN: I couldn't either at first but it's true. I saw Master Windu attempt to assassinate the Chancellor myself.
Dialogue: I couldn't either at first but it's true. I saw Master Windu attempt to assassinate the Chancellor myself.

Script: C-3PO: Something important is going on! I heard a rumor they are going to banish all droids.
Dialogue: Something important is going on! I heard a rumor they are going to banish all droids.

Script: C-3PO: (continuing) Shhhhhh . . . not so loud.
Dialogue: Shhhhhh . . . not so loud.

Script: C-3PO: (continuing) Whatever it is we'll be the last to know.
Dialogue: Whatever it is we'll be the last to know.

Script: PADME: Anakin what are you going to do?
Dialogue: Anakin what are you going to do?

Script: ANAKIN: I will not betray the Republic . . . my loyalties lie with the Chancellor and with the Senate . . . and with you.
Dialogue: I will not betray the Republic . . . my loyalties lie with the Chancellor and with the Senate . . . and with you.

Script: PADME: What about Obi-Wan?
Dialogue: What about Obi-Wan?

Script: ANAKIN: I don't know . . . Many Jedi have been killed. We can only hope that he's remained loyal to the Chancellor.
Dialogue: I don't know . . . Many Jedi have been killed. We can only hope that he's remained loyal to the Chancellor.

Script: PADME: How could this have happened?
Dialogue: How could this have happened?

Script: ANAKIN: The Republic is unstable Padme. The Jedi aren't the only ones trying to take advantage of the situation. There are also traitors in the Senate.
Dialogue: The Republic is unstable Padme. The Jedi aren't the only ones trying to take advantage of the situation. There are also traitors in the Senate.

Script: PADME: What are you saying?
Dialogue: What are you saying?

Script: ANAKIN: You need to distance yourself from your friends in the Senate. The Chancellor said they will be dealt with when this conflict is over.
Dialogue: You need to distance yourself from your friends in the Senate. The Chancellor said they will be dealt with when this conflict is over.

Script: PADME: What if they start an inquisition? I've opposed this war. What will you do if I become a suspect?
Dialogue: What if they start an inquisition? I've opposed this war. What will you do if I become a suspect?

Script: ANAKIN: That won't happen. I won't let it.
Dialogue: That won't happen. I won't let it.

Script: PADME: Oh Anakin I'm afraid.
Dialogue: Oh Anakin I'm afraid.

Script: ANAKIN: Have faith my love. Everything will soon be set right. The Chancellor has given me a very important mission. The Separatists have gathered in the Mustafar system. I'm going there to end this war. Wait for me until I return . . . things will be different I promise.
Dialogue: Have faith my love. Everything will soon be set right. The Chancellor has given me a very important mission. The Separatists have gathered in the Mustafar system. I'm going there to end this war. Wait for me until I return . . . things will be different I promise.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) Please wait for me.
Dialogue: Please wait for me.

Script: PADME: I will.
Dialogue: I will.

Script: C-3PO: (to Artoo) Well he is under a lot of stress Artoo.
Dialogue: Well he is under a lot of stress Artoo.

Script: C-3PO: (continuing) Take care my little friend.
Dialogue: Take care my little friend.

Script: C-3PO: (continuing) My Lady is there anything I might do?
Dialogue: My Lady is there anything I might do?

Script: PADME: No thank you Threepio.
Dialogue: No thank you Threepio.

Script: G-3PO: A snack perhaps?
Dialogue: A snack perhaps?

Script: PADME: No.
Dialogue: No.

Script: C-3PO: I feel so helpless.
Dialogue: I feel so helpless.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: You made it.
Dialogue: You made it.

Script: YODA: Master Kenobi dark times are these. Good to see you. it is.
Dialogue: Master Kenobi dark times are these. Good to see you. it is.

Script: OBI-WAN: You were attacked by your Clones also?
Dialogue: You were attacked by your Clones also?

Script: YODA: With the help of the Wookiees barely escape I did.
Dialogue: With the help of the Wookiees barely escape I did.

Script: OBI-WAN: How many other Jedi managed to survive?
Dialogue: How many other Jedi managed to survive?

Script: YODA: Heard from no one have we.
Dialogue: Heard from no one have we.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: I saw thousands of troops attack the Jedi Temple. That's why I went looking for Yoda.
Dialogue: I saw thousands of troops attack the Jedi Temple. That's why I went looking for Yoda.

Script: OBI-WAN: Have we had any contact from the Temple?
Dialogue: Have we had any contact from the Temple?

Script: YODA: Received a coded retreat message we have.
Dialogue: Received a coded retreat message we have.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: It requests all Jedi to return to the Temple. It says that the war is over . . .
Dialogue: It requests all Jedi to return to the Temple. It says that the war is over . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Well then we must go back! If there are other stragglers they will fall into the trap and be killed.
Dialogue: Well then we must go back! If there are other stragglers they will fall into the trap and be killed.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: It's too dangerous to return.
Dialogue: It's too dangerous to return.

Script: YODA: Suggest dismantling the coded signal do you?
Dialogue: Suggest dismantling the coded signal do you?

Script: OBI-WAN: Yes Master. There is too much at stake here and we need a clearer picture of what has happened.
Dialogue: Yes Master. There is too much at stake here and we need a clearer picture of what has happened.

Script: YODA: I agree. In a dark place we find ourselves ... a little more knowledge might light our way.
Dialogue: I agree. In a dark place we find ourselves ... a little more knowledge might light our way.

Script: NUTE GUNRAY: The plan has gone as you had promised My Lord.
Dialogue: The plan has gone as you had promised My Lord.

Script: DARTH SIDIOUS: You have done well Viceroy. When my new apprentice Darth Vader arrives he will take care of you.
Dialogue: You have done well Viceroy. When my new apprentice Darth Vader arrives he will take care of you.

Script: PILOT: We are receiving a message from the Chancellor's office sir.
Dialogue: We are receiving a message from the Chancellor's office sir.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Send it through.
Dialogue: Send it through.

Script: PILOT: Yes sir.
Dialogue: Yes sir.

Script: MAS AMEDDA: Senator Organa . . . the Supreme Chancellor of the Republic requests your presence at a special session of Congress.
Dialogue: Senator Organa . . . the Supreme Chancellor of the Republic requests your presence at a special session of Congress.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Tell the Chancellor I will be there.
Dialogue: Tell the Chancellor I will be there.

Script: MAS AMEDDA: Very well. He will be expecting you.
Dialogue: Very well. He will be expecting you.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: It could be a trap.
Dialogue: It could be a trap.

Script: OBI-WAN: No I don't think so. The Chancellor will not be able to control the thousands of star systems without keeping the Senate intact.
Dialogue: No I don't think so. The Chancellor will not be able to control the thousands of star systems without keeping the Senate intact.

Script: YODA: If a special session of Congress there is easier for us to enter the Jedi Temple it will be.
Dialogue: If a special session of Congress there is easier for us to enter the Jedi Temple it will be.

Script: GUARD: Welcome back Senator. May I see your clearance?
Dialogue: Welcome back Senator. May I see your clearance?

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Certainly.
Dialogue: Certainly.

Script: GUARD: Thank you you may proceed. We will take custody of the Jedi.
Dialogue: Thank you you may proceed. We will take custody of the Jedi.

Script: OBI-WAN: It would be better if we stayed with the Senator.
Dialogue: It would be better if we stayed with the Senator.

Script: GUARD: It would be better if they stayed with you.
Dialogue: It would be better if they stayed with you.

Script: ANAKIN: Artoo . . . stay with the ship.
Dialogue: Artoo . . . stay with the ship.

Script: NUTE GUNRAY: Welcome Lord Vader. We've been expecting you.
Dialogue: Welcome Lord Vader. We've been expecting you.

Script: OBI-WAN: There are several battalions of Clone Troopers on every level. Many are dressed as Jedi.
Dialogue: There are several battalions of Clone Troopers on every level. Many are dressed as Jedi.

Script: YODA: Dismantle the coded signal quickly. That group back there soon discovered will be.
Dialogue: Dismantle the coded signal quickly. That group back there soon discovered will be.

Script: PALPATINE: . . . and the Jedi Rebellion has been foiled.
Dialogue: . . . and the Jedi Rebellion has been foiled.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: I was held up. What's happening?
Dialogue: I was held up. What's happening?

Script: PADME: The Chancellor has been elaborating on a plot by the Jedi to overthrow the Senate.
Dialogue: The Chancellor has been elaborating on a plot by the Jedi to overthrow the Senate.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: That's not true!
Dialogue: That's not true!

Script: PADME: He's been presenting evidence all afternoon.
Dialogue: He's been presenting evidence all afternoon.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: And the Senate will go along with it just like they always do.
Dialogue: And the Senate will go along with it just like they always do.

Script: PALPATINE: The remaining Jedi will be hunted down and defeated. (applause) Any collaborators will suffer the same fate.
Dialogue: The remaining Jedi will be hunted down and defeated.  Any collaborators will suffer the same fate.

Script: OBI-WAN: Not even the younglings survived.
Dialogue: Not even the younglings survived.

Script: YODA: Killed not by clones this Padawan. By a lightsaber he was.
Dialogue: Killed not by clones this Padawan. By a lightsaber he was.

Script: OBI-WAN: . . .Who?? Who could have done this?
Dialogue: . . .Who?? Who could have done this?

Script: PALPATINE: The attempt on my life has left me scarred and deformed but I assure you my resolve has never been stronger.
Dialogue: The attempt on my life has left me scarred and deformed but I assure you my resolve has never been stronger.

Script: PALPATINE: The war is over. (applause) The Separatists have been defeated (applause) and the Jedi rebellion has been foiled. We stand on the threshold of a new beginning.
Dialogue: The war is over.  and the Jedi rebellion has been foiled. We stand on the threshold of a new beginning.

Script: PADME: Well this is the moment we discover if he intends to return the Republic to a democracy.
Dialogue: Well this is the moment we discover if he intends to return the Republic to a democracy.

Script: PALPATINE: In order to ensure our security and continuing stability the Republic will be reorganized into the first Galactic Empire for a safe and secure society which I assure you will last for ten thousand years.
Dialogue: In order to ensure our security and continuing stability the Republic will be reorganized into the first Galactic Empire for a safe and secure society which I assure you will last for ten thousand years.

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) An empire that will continue to be ruled by this august body and a sovereign ruler chosen for life . . .
Dialogue: An empire that will continue to be ruled by this august body and a sovereign ruler chosen for life . . .

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) An empire ruled by the majority . . . Ruled by a new constitution . . .
Dialogue: An empire ruled by the majority . . . Ruled by a new constitution . . .

Script: PADME: So this is how liberty dies with thunderous applause . . .
Dialogue: So this is how liberty dies with thunderous applause . . .

Script: BAIL ORGANA: We cannot let this happen.
Dialogue: We cannot let this happen.

Script: PADME: Not now! There will be a time.
Dialogue: Not now! There will be a time.

Script: RUNE HAAKO: Stop! Enough this is not right!
Dialogue: Stop! Enough this is not right!

Script: NUTE GUNRAY: The war is over. Lord Sidious promised us peace ... we only want . . .
Dialogue: The war is over. Lord Sidious promised us peace ... we only want . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: I've recalibrated the code warning all surviving Jedi to stay away.
Dialogue: I've recalibrated the code warning all surviving Jedi to stay away.

Script: YODA: Good . . . For the Clones to discover the recalibration a long time it will take. To change it back longer still. Hurry.
Dialogue: Good . . . For the Clones to discover the recalibration a long time it will take. To change it back longer still. Hurry.

Script: OBI-WAN: Wait Master. There is something I must know . . .
Dialogue: Wait Master. There is something I must know . . .

Script: YODA: If into the security recordings you go only pain will you find.
Dialogue: If into the security recordings you go only pain will you find.

Script: OBI-WAN: I must know the truth Master.
Dialogue: I must know the truth Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) It can't be . . . It can't be . . .
Dialogue: It can't be . . . It can't be . . .

Script: ANAKIN: The traitors have been taken care of Lord Sidious.
Dialogue: The traitors have been taken care of Lord Sidious.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Good . . . good . . . You have done well my new apprentice. Do you feel your power growing?
Dialogue: Good . . . good . . . You have done well my new apprentice. Do you feel your power growing?

Script: ANAKIN: Yes My Master.
Dialogue: Yes My Master.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Now Lord Vader now go and bring peace to the Empire.
Dialogue: Now Lord Vader now go and bring peace to the Empire.

Script: OBI-WAN: I can't watch any more.
Dialogue: I can't watch any more.

Script: YODA: Destroy the Sith we must.
Dialogue: Destroy the Sith we must.

Script: OBI-WAN: Send me to kill the Emperor. I will not kill Anakin.
Dialogue: Send me to kill the Emperor. I will not kill Anakin.

Script: YODA: To fight this Lord Sidious strong enough you are not.
Dialogue: To fight this Lord Sidious strong enough you are not.

Script: OBI-WAN: He is like my brother ... I cannot do it.
Dialogue: He is like my brother ... I cannot do it.

Script: YODA: Twisted by the dark side young Skywalker has become. The boy you trained gone he is . . . Consumed by Darth Vader.
Dialogue: Twisted by the dark side young Skywalker has become. The boy you trained gone he is . . . Consumed by Darth Vader.

Script: OBI-WAN: How could it have come to this?
Dialogue: How could it have come to this?

Script: YODA: To question no time there is.
Dialogue: To question no time there is.

Script: OBI-WAN: I do not know where the Emperor has sent him. I don't know where to look.
Dialogue: I do not know where the Emperor has sent him. I don't know where to look.

Script: YODA: Use your feelings Obi-Wan and find him you will. Visit the new Emperor my task is. May the Force be with you.
Dialogue: Use your feelings Obi-Wan and find him you will. Visit the new Emperor my task is. May the Force be with you.

Script: OBI-WAN: May the Force be with you Master Yoda.
Dialogue: May the Force be with you Master Yoda.

Script: C-3PO: Hello might I help you . . . Oh it's you Master Kenobi. Come in quickly.
Dialogue: Hello might I help you . . . Oh it's you Master Kenobi. Come in quickly.

Script: OBI-WAN: Has Anakin been here . . . ?
Dialogue: Has Anakin been here . . . ?

Script: C-3PO: Yes . . . right after the attack on the Jedi Temple.
Dialogue: Yes . . . right after the attack on the Jedi Temple.

Script: PADME: Master Kenobi . . .
Dialogue: Master Kenobi . . .

Script: PADME: (continuing) Oh Obi-Wan thank goodness . . . you're alive.
Dialogue: Oh Obi-Wan thank goodness . . . you're alive.

Script: OBI-WAN: The Republic has fallen. Padme . . . The Jedi Order is no more . . .
Dialogue: The Republic has fallen. Padme . . . The Jedi Order is no more . . .

Script: PADME: I know it's hard to believe everything to which we've dedicated our lives is gone.
Dialogue: I know it's hard to believe everything to which we've dedicated our lives is gone.

Script: OBI-WAN: I believe we have been part of a plot hundreds of years in the making.
Dialogue: I believe we have been part of a plot hundreds of years in the making.

Script: PADME: The Senate is still intact there is some hope.
Dialogue: The Senate is still intact there is some hope.

Script: OBI-WAN: No. Padme . . . It's over . . . The Sith now rule the galaxy as they did before the Republic.
Dialogue: No. Padme . . . It's over . . . The Sith now rule the galaxy as they did before the Republic.

Script: PADME: The Sith!?!
Dialogue: The Sith!?!

Script: OBI-WAN: I'm here looking for Anakin . . . When was the last time you saw him?
Dialogue: I'm here looking for Anakin . . . When was the last time you saw him?

Script: PADME: Yesterday.
Dialogue: Yesterday.

Script: OBI-WAN: And do you know where he is now?
Dialogue: And do you know where he is now?

Script: PADME: (looks down) No.
Dialogue: No.

Script: OBI-WAN: Padme I need your help. He's in grave danger.
Dialogue: Padme I need your help. He's in grave danger.

Script: PADME: From the Sith?
Dialogue: From the Sith?

Script: OBI-WAN: From himself . . . Padme Anakin has turned to the dark side.
Dialogue: From himself . . . Padme Anakin has turned to the dark side.

Script: PADME: You're wrong! How could you even say that?
Dialogue: You're wrong! How could you even say that?

Script: OBI-WAN: I have seen a security hologram of him killing younglings.
Dialogue: I have seen a security hologram of him killing younglings.

Script: PADME: Not Anakin! He couldn't!
Dialogue: Not Anakin! He couldn't!

Script: OBI-WAN: He was deceived by a lie. We all were. It appears that the Chancellor is behind everything including the war. Palpatine is the Sith Lord we've been looking for. After the death of Count Dooku Anakin became his new apprentice.
Dialogue: He was deceived by a lie. We all were. It appears that the Chancellor is behind everything including the war. Palpatine is the Sith Lord we've been looking for. After the death of Count Dooku Anakin became his new apprentice.

Script: PADME: I don't believe you ... I can't.
Dialogue: I don't believe you ... I can't.

Script: OBI-WAN: Padme I must find him.
Dialogue: Padme I must find him.

Script: PADME: You're going to kill him aren't you?
Dialogue: You're going to kill him aren't you?

Script: OBI-WAN: He has become a very great threat.
Dialogue: He has become a very great threat.

Script: PADME: I can't . . .
Dialogue: I can't . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin is the father isn't he?
Dialogue: Anakin is the father isn't he?

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: I'm so sorry.

Script: CAPTAIN TYPHO: My Lady let me come with you.
Dialogue: My Lady let me come with you.

Script: PADME: There is no danger. The fighting is over and . . . this is personal.
Dialogue: There is no danger. The fighting is over and . . . this is personal.

Script: CAPTAIN TYPHO: As you wish My Lady . . . but I strongly disagree.
Dialogue: As you wish My Lady . . . but I strongly disagree.

Script: PADME: I'll be all right Captain.
Dialogue: I'll be all right Captain.

Script: PADME: (continuing) This is something I must do myself. Besides Threepio will look after me.
Dialogue: This is something I must do myself. Besides Threepio will look after me.

Script: C-3PO: Oh dear.
Dialogue: Oh dear.

Script: C-3PO: Green light. Do you know that I think I'm beginning to get the hang of this flying business.
Dialogue: Green light. Do you know that I think I'm beginning to get the hang of this flying business.

Script: DARTH VADER: The Separatists are taken care of My Master.
Dialogue: The Separatists are taken care of My Master.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: It is finished then. You have restored peace and justice to the galaxy. You have done well Lord Vader.
Dialogue: It is finished then. You have restored peace and justice to the galaxy. You have done well Lord Vader.

Script: DARTH VADER: Thank you My Master.
Dialogue: Thank you My Master.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Send a message to the ships of the Trade Federation. Tell them the Separatist leaders have been wiped out. Grievous and Dooku have been destroyed. All droid units must shut down immediately.
Dialogue: Send a message to the ships of the Trade Federation. Tell them the Separatist leaders have been wiped out. Grievous and Dooku have been destroyed. All droid units must shut down immediately.

Script: DARTH VADER: Very good My Lord.
Dialogue: Very good My Lord.

Script: ANAKIN: Padme I saw your ship . . .
Dialogue: Padme I saw your ship . . .

Script: PADME: Oh Anakin!
Dialogue: Oh Anakin!

Script: ANAKIN: It's all right you're safe now. What are you doing out here?
Dialogue: It's all right you're safe now. What are you doing out here?

Script: PADME: I was so worried about you. Obi-Wan told me terrible things.
Dialogue: I was so worried about you. Obi-Wan told me terrible things.

Script: ANAKIN: What things?
Dialogue: What things?

Script: PADME: He said you have turned to the dark side . . . that you killed younglings.
Dialogue: He said you have turned to the dark side . . . that you killed younglings.

Script: ANAKIN: Obi-Wan is trying to turn you against me.
Dialogue: Obi-Wan is trying to turn you against me.

Script: PADME: He cares about us.
Dialogue: He cares about us.

Script: ANAKIN: Us??!
Dialogue: Us??!

Script: PADME: He knows . . . He wants to help you.
Dialogue: He knows . . . He wants to help you.

Script: ANAKIN: Is Obi-Wan going to protect you? He can't ... he can't help you. He's not strong enough.
Dialogue: Is Obi-Wan going to protect you? He can't ... he can't help you. He's not strong enough.

Script: PADME: Anakin all I want is your love.
Dialogue: Anakin all I want is your love.

Script: ANAKIN: Love won't save you Padme. Only my new powers can do that.
Dialogue: Love won't save you Padme. Only my new powers can do that.

Script: PADME: At what cost? You are a good person. Don't do this.
Dialogue: At what cost? You are a good person. Don't do this.

Script: ANAKIN: I won't lose you the way I lost my mother! I've become more powerful than any Jedi has ever dreamed of and I've done it for you. To protect you.
Dialogue: I won't lose you the way I lost my mother! I've become more powerful than any Jedi has ever dreamed of and I've done it for you. To protect you.

Script: PADME: Come away with me. Help me raise our child. Leave everything else behind while we still can.
Dialogue: Come away with me. Help me raise our child. Leave everything else behind while we still can.

Script: ANAKIN: Don't you see we don't have to run away anymore. I have brought peace to the Republic. I am more powerful than the Chancellor. I can overthrow him and together you and I can rule the galaxy. Make things the way we want them to be.
Dialogue: Don't you see we don't have to run away anymore. I have brought peace to the Republic. I am more powerful than the Chancellor. I can overthrow him and together you and I can rule the galaxy. Make things the way we want them to be.

Script: PADME: I don't believe what I'm hearing . . . Obi-Wan was right. You've changed.
Dialogue: I don't believe what I'm hearing . . . Obi-Wan was right. You've changed.

Script: ANAKIN: I don't want to hear any more about Obi-Wan. The Jedi turned against me. Don't you turn against me.
Dialogue: I don't want to hear any more about Obi-Wan. The Jedi turned against me. Don't you turn against me.

Script:
PADME: I don't know you anymore. Anakin you're breaking my heart. I'll never stop loving you but you are going down a path I
can't follow.
Dialogue:
I don't know you anymore. Anakin you're breaking my heart. I'll never stop loving you but you are going down a path I
can't follow.

Script: ANAKIN: Because of Obi-Wan?
Dialogue: Because of Obi-Wan?

Script: PADME: Because of what you've done . . . what you plan to do. Stop stop now. Come back! I love you.
Dialogue: Because of what you've done . . . what you plan to do. Stop stop now. Come back! I love you.

Script: ANAKIN: (seeing Obi-Wan) Liar!
Dialogue: Liar!

Script: PADME: No!
Dialogue: No!

Script: ANAKIN: You're with him. You've betrayed me! You brought him here to kill me!
Dialogue: You're with him. You've betrayed me! You brought him here to kill me!

Script: PADME: NO! Anakin. I swear ... I ...
Dialogue: NO! Anakin. I swear ... I ...

Script: OBI-WAN: Let her go Anakin.
Dialogue: Let her go Anakin.

Script: ANAKIN: What have you and she been up to?
Dialogue: What have you and she been up to?

Script: OBI-WAN: Let her go!
Dialogue: Let her go!

Script: ANAKIN: You turned her against me.
Dialogue: You turned her against me.

Script: OBI-WAN: You have done that yourself.
Dialogue: You have done that yourself.

Script: ANAKIN: You will not take her from me.
Dialogue: You will not take her from me.

Script: OBI-WAN: Your anger and your lust for power have already done that.
Dialogue: Your anger and your lust for power have already done that.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) You have allowed this Dark Lord to twist your mind until now . . . until now you have become the very thing you swore to destroy.
Dialogue: You have allowed this Dark Lord to twist your mind until now . . . until now you have become the very thing you swore to destroy.

Script: ANAKIN: Don't lecture me Obi-Wan. I see through the lies of the Jedi. I do not fear the dark side as you do. I have brought peace justice freedom and security to my new Empire.
Dialogue: Don't lecture me Obi-Wan. I see through the lies of the Jedi. I do not fear the dark side as you do. I have brought peace justice freedom and security to my new Empire.

Script: OBI-WAN: Your new Empire?
Dialogue: Your new Empire?

Script: ANAKIN: Don't make me kill you.
Dialogue: Don't make me kill you.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin my allegiance is to the Republic ... to democracy.
Dialogue: Anakin my allegiance is to the Republic ... to democracy.

Script: ANAKIN: If you're not with me you're my enemy.
Dialogue: If you're not with me you're my enemy.

Script: OBI-WAN: Only a Sith Lord deals in absolutes. I will do what I must.
Dialogue: Only a Sith Lord deals in absolutes. I will do what I must.

Script: ANAKIN: You will try.
Dialogue: You will try.

Script: YODA: I hear a new apprentice you have. Emperor or should I call you Darth Sidious.
Dialogue: I hear a new apprentice you have. Emperor or should I call you Darth Sidious.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Master Yoda you survived.
Dialogue: Master Yoda you survived.

Script: YODA: Surprised?
Dialogue: Surprised?

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: Your arrogance blinds you Master Yoda. Now you will experience the full power of the dark side.
Dialogue: Your arrogance blinds you Master Yoda. Now you will experience the full power of the dark side.

Script: C-3PO: What are you doing? You're going to hurt her. Wait!!
Dialogue: What are you doing? You're going to hurt her. Wait!!

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: I have waited a long time for this moment my little green friend. At last the Jedi are no more.
Dialogue: I have waited a long time for this moment my little green friend. At last the Jedi are no more.

Script: YODA: Not if anything I have to say about it Lord Sidious.
Dialogue: Not if anything I have to say about it Lord Sidious.

Script: YODA: (continuing) At an end your rule is and not short enough it was I must say.
Dialogue: At an end your rule is and not short enough it was I must say.

Script: YODA: (continuing) If so powerful you are why leave??
Dialogue: If so powerful you are why leave??

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: You will not stop me. Darth Vader will become more powerful than either of us.
Dialogue: You will not stop me. Darth Vader will become more powerful than either of us.

Script: YODA: Faith in your new apprentice misplaced may be as is your faith in the dark side of the Force.
Dialogue: Faith in your new apprentice misplaced may be as is your faith in the dark side of the Force.

Script: ANAKIN: Don't make me destroy you Master. You're no match for the dark side.
Dialogue: Don't make me destroy you Master. You're no match for the dark side.

Script: OBI-WAN: I've heard that before Anakin . . . but I never thought I'd hear it from you.
Dialogue: I've heard that before Anakin . . . but I never thought I'd hear it from you.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) The flaw of power is arrogance.
Dialogue: The flaw of power is arrogance.

Script: ANAKIN: You hesitate . . . the flaw of compassion.
Dialogue: You hesitate . . . the flaw of compassion.

Script: YODA: Destroy you I will just as Master Kenobi your apprentice will destroy.
Dialogue: Destroy you I will just as Master Kenobi your apprentice will destroy.

Script: YODA: Hurry. Careful timing we will need.
Dialogue: Hurry. Careful timing we will need.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: (in speeder) There aren't many troops on this side. Activate your homing beacon when you're ready.
Dialogue: There aren't many troops on this side. Activate your homing beacon when you're ready.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER THIRE: There is no sign of his body sir.
Dialogue: There is no sign of his body sir.

Script: MAS AMEDDA: Then he is not dead.
Dialogue: Then he is not dead.

Script: PALPATINE: Double your search.
Dialogue: Double your search.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER THIRE: Yes sir. Right away sir.
Dialogue: Yes sir. Right away sir.

Script: PALPATINE: (to Mas Amedda) Tell Captain Kagi to prepare my shuttle for immediate takeoff.
Dialogue: Tell Captain Kagi to prepare my shuttle for immediate takeoff.

Script: MAS AMEDDA: Yes Master.
Dialogue: Yes Master.

Script: PALPATINE: I sense Lord Vader is in danger.
Dialogue: I sense Lord Vader is in danger.

Script: YODA: Into exile I must go. Failed I have.
Dialogue: Into exile I must go. Failed I have.

Script: C-3PO: I am being careful. I've got a good hold on her but . . . I'm worried about my back. I hope it's able to hold up under this weight.
Dialogue: I am being careful. I've got a good hold on her but . . . I'm worried about my back. I hope it's able to hold up under this weight.

Script: OBI-WAN: I have failed you Anakin. I was never able to teach you to think.
Dialogue: I have failed you Anakin. I was never able to teach you to think.

Script: ANAKIN: I should have known the Jedi were plotting to take over . . .
Dialogue: I should have known the Jedi were plotting to take over . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: From the Sith!!! Anakin Chancellor Palpatine is evil.
Dialogue: From the Sith!!! Anakin Chancellor Palpatine is evil.

Script: ANAKIN: From the Jedi point of view! From my point of view the Jedi are evil.
Dialogue: From the Jedi point of view! From my point of view the Jedi are evil.

Script: OBI-WAN: Well then you are lost!
Dialogue: Well then you are lost!

Script: ANAKIN: This is the end for you My Master. I wish it were otherwise.
Dialogue: This is the end for you My Master. I wish it were otherwise.

Script: OBI-WAN: It's over Anakin. I have the high ground.
Dialogue: It's over Anakin. I have the high ground.

Script: ANAKIN: You underestimate my power!
Dialogue: You underestimate my power!

Script: OBI-WAN: Don't try it.
Dialogue: Don't try it.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) . . . You were the Chosen One! It was said that you would destroy the Sith not join them. It was you who would bring balance to the Force not leave it in Darkness.
Dialogue: . . . You were the Chosen One! It was said that you would destroy the Sith not join them. It was you who would bring balance to the Force not leave it in Darkness.

Script: ANAKIN: I hate you!
Dialogue: I hate you!

Script: OBI-WAN: You were my brother Anakin. I loved you.
Dialogue: You were my brother Anakin. I loved you.

Script: C-3PO: Master Kenobi! We have Miss Padme on board. Please please hurry. We should leave this dreadful place.
Dialogue: Master Kenobi! We have Miss Padme on board. Please please hurry. We should leave this dreadful place.

Script: PADME: Obi-Wan? Is Anakin all right?
Dialogue: Obi-Wan? Is Anakin all right?

Script: DARTH SIDIOUS: Anakin! Anakin! There he is. He's still alive. Get a medical capsule immediately.
Dialogue: Anakin! Anakin! There he is. He's still alive. Get a medical capsule immediately.

Script: CLONE CAPTAIN: Yes sir. Right away.
Dialogue: Yes sir. Right away.

Script: YODA: Failed to stop the Sith Lord I have. Still much to learn there is ...
Dialogue: Failed to stop the Sith Lord I have. Still much to learn there is ...

Script: QUI -GON: (V.O.) Patience. You will have time. I did not. When I became one with the Force I made a great discovery. With my training you will be able to merge with the Force at will. Your physical self will fade away but you will still retain your consciousness. You will become more powerful than any Sith.
Dialogue: Patience. You will have time. I did not. When I became one with the Force I made a great discovery. With my training you will be able to merge with the Force at will. Your physical self will fade away but you will still retain your consciousness. You will become more powerful than any Sith.

Script: YODA: Eternal consciousness.
Dialogue: Eternal consciousness.

Script: QUI-GON: (V.O.) The ability to defy oblivion can be achieved but only for oneself. It was accomplished by a Shaman of the Whills. It is a state acquired through compassion not greed.
Dialogue: The ability to defy oblivion can be achieved but only for oneself. It was accomplished by a Shaman of the Whills. It is a state acquired through compassion not greed.

Script: YODA: . . . to become one with the Force and influence still have . . . A power greater than all it is.
Dialogue: . . . to become one with the Force and influence still have . . . A power greater than all it is.

Script: QUI-GON: (V.O.) You will learn to let go of everything. No attachment no thought of self. No physical self.
Dialogue: You will learn to let go of everything. No attachment no thought of self. No physical self.

Script: YODA: A great Jedi Master you have become Qui-Gon Jinn. Your apprentice I gratefully become.
Dialogue: A great Jedi Master you have become Qui-Gon Jinn. Your apprentice I gratefully become.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Excuse me Master Yoda. Obi-Wan Kenobi has made contact.
Dialogue: Excuse me Master Yoda. Obi-Wan Kenobi has made contact.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: We'll take her to the medical center quickly.
Dialogue: We'll take her to the medical center quickly.

Script: MEDICAL DROID: Medically she is completely healthy. For reasons we can't explain we are losing her.
Dialogue: Medically she is completely healthy. For reasons we can't explain we are losing her.

Script: OBI-WAN: She's dying?
Dialogue: She's dying?

Script: MEDICAL DROID: We don't know why. She has lost the will to live. We need to operate quickly if we are to save the babies.
Dialogue: We don't know why. She has lost the will to live. We need to operate quickly if we are to save the babies.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Babies??!!
Dialogue: Babies??!!

Script: MEDICAL DROID: She's carrying twins.
Dialogue: She's carrying twins.

Script: YODA: Save them we must. They are our last hope.
Dialogue: Save them we must. They are our last hope.

Script: C-3PO: It s some kind of reproductive process I think.
Dialogue: It s some kind of reproductive process I think.

Script: OBI-WAN: Don't give up Padme.
Dialogue: Don't give up Padme.

Script: MEDICAL DROID: It's a boy.
Dialogue: It's a boy.

Script: PADME: Luke . . .
Dialogue: Luke . . .

Script: MEDICAL DROID: ... and a girl.
Dialogue: ... and a girl.

Script: PADME: . . . Leia.
Dialogue: . . . Leia.

Script: OBI-WAN: You have twins Padme They need you . . . hang on.
Dialogue: You have twins Padme They need you . . . hang on.

Script: PADME: I can't . . .
Dialogue: I can't . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Save your energy.
Dialogue: Save your energy.

Script: PADME: Obi-Wan . . . there . . . is good in him. I know there is ... still . . .
Dialogue: Obi-Wan . . . there . . . is good in him. I know there is ... still . . .

Script: MEDICAL DROID: My Lord the construction is finished ... he lives.
Dialogue: My Lord the construction is finished ... he lives.

Script: DARTH SIDIOUS: Good. Good.
Dialogue: Good. Good.

Script: DARTH SIDIOUS: (continuing) Lord Vader can you hear me?
Dialogue: Lord Vader can you hear me?

Script: DARTH VADER: Yes My Master.
Dialogue: Yes My Master.

Script: DARTH VADER: (continuing) Where is Padme? Is she safe is she all right?
Dialogue: Where is Padme? Is she safe is she all right?

Script: DARTH SIDIOUS: I'm afraid she died. ... it seems in your anger you killed her.
Dialogue: I'm afraid she died. ... it seems in your anger you killed her.

Script: DARTH VADER: I couldn't have! She was alive! I felt her! She was alive! It's impossible! No!!!
Dialogue: I couldn't have! She was alive! I felt her! She was alive! It's impossible! No!!!

Script: YODA: Pregnant she must still appear. Hidden safe the children must be kept.
Dialogue: Pregnant she must still appear. Hidden safe the children must be kept.

Script: OBI-WAN: We must take them somewhere the Sith will not sense their presence.
Dialogue: We must take them somewhere the Sith will not sense their presence.

Script: YODA: Split up they should be.
Dialogue: Split up they should be.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: My wife and I will take the girl. We've always talked of adopting a baby girl. She will be loved with us.
Dialogue: My wife and I will take the girl. We've always talked of adopting a baby girl. She will be loved with us.

Script: OBI-WAN: And what of the boy?
Dialogue: And what of the boy?

Script: YODA: To Tatooine. To his family send him.
Dialogue: To Tatooine. To his family send him.

Script: OBI-WAN: I will take the child and watch over him. Master Yoda do you think Anakin's twins will be able to defeat Darth Sidious?
Dialogue: I will take the child and watch over him. Master Yoda do you think Anakin's twins will be able to defeat Darth Sidious?

Script: YODA: Strong the Force runs in the Skywalker line. Hope we can . . . Done it is. Until the time is right disappear we will.
Dialogue: Strong the Force runs in the Skywalker line. Hope we can . . . Done it is. Until the time is right disappear we will.

Script: YODA: (continuing) Master Kenobi wait a moment. In your solitude on Tatooine training I have for you.
Dialogue: Master Kenobi wait a moment. In your solitude on Tatooine training I have for you.

Script: OBI-WAN: Training??
Dialogue: Training??

Script: YODA: An old friend has learned the path to immortality.
Dialogue: An old friend has learned the path to immortality.

Script: OBI-WAN: Who?
Dialogue: Who?

Script: YODA: One who has returned from the netherworld of the Force to train me . . . your old Master Qui-Gon Jinn.
Dialogue: One who has returned from the netherworld of the Force to train me . . . your old Master Qui-Gon Jinn.

Script: OBI-WAN: Qui-Gon? But how could he accomplish this?
Dialogue: Qui-Gon? But how could he accomplish this?

Script: YODA: The secret of the Ancient Order of the Whills he studied. How to commune with him. I will teach you.
Dialogue: The secret of the Ancient Order of the Whills he studied. How to commune with him. I will teach you.

Script: OBI-WAN: I will be able to talk with him?
Dialogue: I will be able to talk with him?

Script: YODA: How to join the Force he will train you. Your consciousness you will retain when one with the Force. Even your physical self perhaps.
Dialogue: How to join the Force he will train you. Your consciousness you will retain when one with the Force. Even your physical self perhaps.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Captain Antilles.
Dialogue: Captain Antilles.

Script: CAPTAIN ANTILLES: Yes Your Highness.
Dialogue: Yes Your Highness.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: I'm placing these droids in your care. Treat them well. Clean them up. Have the Protocol Droid's mind wiped.
Dialogue: I'm placing these droids in your care. Treat them well. Clean them up. Have the Protocol Droid's mind wiped.

Script: C-3PO: Oh no.
Dialogue: Oh no.

Script: ANAKIN: There isn't a droid made that can out fly you Master and no other way to get to the Chancellor . . .
Dialogue: There isn't a droid made that can out fly you Master and no other way to get to the Chancellor . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Look out four droids inbound . . .
Dialogue: Look out four droids inbound . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: We've got to split them up.
Dialogue: We've got to split them up.

Script: ANAKIN: Break left fly through the guns on that tower.
Dialogue: Break left fly through the guns on that tower.

Script: OBI-WAN: Easy for you to say . . . why am I always the bait?
Dialogue: Easy for you to say . . . why am I always the bait?

Script: ANAKIN: Don't worry. I'm coming around behind you.
Dialogue: Don't worry. I'm coming around behind you.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin they're all over me!
Dialogue: Anakin they're all over me!

Script: ANAKIN: Dead ahead! Closing . . . lock onto him Artoo . . .
Dialogue: Dead ahead! Closing . . . lock onto him Artoo . . .

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing laughs) We got him Artoo!
Dialogue: We got him Artoo!

Script: ANAKIN: I copy Artoo.
Dialogue: I copy Artoo.

Script: OBI-WAN: I'm going down on the deck.
Dialogue: I'm going down on the deck.

Script: ANAKIN: Good idea ... I need some room to maneuver.
Dialogue: Good idea ... I need some room to maneuver.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) Cut right. Do you hear me?! Cut right. Don't let him get a handle on you. Come on Artoo lock on! Lock on!
Dialogue: Cut right. Do you hear me?! Cut right. Don't let him get a handle on you. Come on Artoo lock on! Lock on!

Script: OBI-WAN: Hurry up! I don't like this!
Dialogue: Hurry up! I don't like this!

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) Ouch!
Dialogue: Ouch!

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) Don't even try to fix it Arfour. I've shut it down.
Dialogue: Don't even try to fix it Arfour. I've shut it down.

Script: ANAKIN: We're locked on ... we've got him . . .
Dialogue: We're locked on ... we've got him . . .

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) Yeah! We got him . . . good going Artoo.
Dialogue: Yeah! We got him . . . good going Artoo.

Script: OBI-WAN: Next time you're the bait . . . Now let's find the Command Ship and get on with it ...
Dialogue: Next time you're the bait . . . Now let's find the Command Ship and get on with it ...

Script: ANAKIN: Lock onto them Artoo. Master General Grievous's ship is directly ahead.
Dialogue: Lock onto them Artoo. Master General Grievous's ship is directly ahead.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) The one crawling with vulture droids.
Dialogue: The one crawling with vulture droids.

Script: OBI-WAN: I see it. Oh this is going to be easy.
Dialogue: I see it. Oh this is going to be easy.

Script: ANAKIN: Come on Master.
Dialogue: Come on Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: Not this time. There's too much at stake. We need help. Odd Ball do you copy?
Dialogue: Not this time. There's too much at stake. We need help. Odd Ball do you copy?

Script: ODD BALL: (OS) Copy Red Leader.
Dialogue: Copy Red Leader.

Script: OBI-WAN: Mark my position and form your squad up behind me . . .
Dialogue: Mark my position and form your squad up behind me . . .

Script: ODD BALL: We're on your tail General Kenobi. Set S-foils in attack position.
Dialogue: We're on your tail General Kenobi. Set S-foils in attack position.

Script: ANAKIN: This is where the fun begins. Ten Vulture Droids straight ahead coming down the left side.
Dialogue: This is where the fun begins. Ten Vulture Droids straight ahead coming down the left side.

Script: OBI-WAN: Add five Tri-fighters on the right . . .
Dialogue: Add five Tri-fighters on the right . . .

Script: ANAKIN: I'm going head to head. See you.
Dialogue: I'm going head to head. See you.

Script: OBI-WAN: Take it easy Anakin.
Dialogue: Take it easy Anakin.

Script: ODD BALL: I'm on your right Red Leader.
Dialogue: I'm on your right Red Leader.

Script: ANAKIN: Incoming!!
Dialogue: Incoming!!

Script: OBI-WAN: Five more on the right!
Dialogue: Five more on the right!

Script: ANAKIN: Here we go.
Dialogue: Here we go.

Script: OBI-WAN: I'm going high and right.
Dialogue: I'm going high and right.

Script: ANAKIN: Hang on. There are four more of them.
Dialogue: Hang on. There are four more of them.

Script: OBI-WAN: Stay with me . . . swing back and right . . . help me engage. Back off ... Let them pass between us.
Dialogue: Stay with me . . . swing back and right . . . help me engage. Back off ... Let them pass between us.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm coming around. I'm coming around on your tail.
Dialogue: I'm coming around. I'm coming around on your tail.

Script: OBI-WAN: All right engage . . . and hurry. These droids are all over me like a rash.
Dialogue: All right engage . . . and hurry. These droids are all over me like a rash.

Script: ANAKIN: How many back there. Artoo? (Artoo beeps) Three . . . (continuing) Four . . . that's not good.
Dialogue: How many back there. Artoo?  Four . . . that's not good.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin you have four on your tail.
Dialogue: Anakin you have four on your tail.

Script: ANAKIN: I know. I know!
Dialogue: I know. I know!

Script: OBI-WAN: Four more closing from your left.
Dialogue: Four more closing from your left.

Script: ANAKIN: I know. I know!
Dialogue: I know. I know!

Script: OBI-WAN: Break right and go high.
Dialogue: Break right and go high.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm going low and left.
Dialogue: I'm going low and left.

Script: OBI-WAN: (to himself) He still has much to learn.
Dialogue: He still has much to learn.

Script: ANAKIN: Hang on Artoo. Obi-Wan do you copy? I'm going to pull them through the needle . . .
Dialogue: Hang on Artoo. Obi-Wan do you copy? I'm going to pull them through the needle . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Too dangerous. First Jedi rule: "Survive."
Dialogue: Too dangerous. First Jedi rule: "Survive."

Script: ANAKIN: Sorry no choice. Come down here and thin them out a little.
Dialogue: Sorry no choice. Come down here and thin them out a little.

Script: OBI-WAN: Just keep me steady . . . hold on ... not yet. . . now break left.
Dialogue: Just keep me steady . . . hold on ... not yet. . . now break left.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) You'll never get through there Anakin. It's too tight.
Dialogue: You'll never get through there Anakin. It's too tight.

Script: ANAKIN: Easy Artoo . . . we've done this before.
Dialogue: Easy Artoo . . . we've done this before.

Script: OBI-WAN: Use the Force think yourself through the ship will follow.
Dialogue: Use the Force think yourself through the ship will follow.

Script: ANAKIN: Wrong thought Artoo.
Dialogue: Wrong thought Artoo.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) I'm through.
Dialogue: I'm through.

Script: ODD BALL: There are too many of them.
Dialogue: There are too many of them.

Script: CLONE PILOT 2: I'm on your wing. Break left. Break left. They're all over me. Get them off my . . .
Dialogue: I'm on your wing. Break left. Break left. They're all over me. Get them off my . . .

Script: ANAKIN: I'm going to go help them out!
Dialogue: I'm going to go help them out!

Script: OBI-WAN: No no! They are doing their job so we can do ours. Head for the Command Ship!
Dialogue: No no! They are doing their job so we can do ours. Head for the Command Ship!

Script: ANAKIN: Missiles! Pull up!
Dialogue: Missiles! Pull up!

Script: OBI-WAN: They overshot us . . .
Dialogue: They overshot us . . .

Script: ANAKIN: They're coming around!
Dialogue: They're coming around!

Script: OBI-WAN: All right Arfour. No no. Nothing too fancy.
Dialogue: All right Arfour. No no. Nothing too fancy.

Script: ANAKIN: Surge all power units. Artoo! Stand by the reverse thrusters.
Dialogue: Surge all power units. Artoo! Stand by the reverse thrusters.

Script: ANAKIN: We got 'em. Artoo!
Dialogue: We got 'em. Artoo!

Script: OBI-WAN: Flying is for droids.
Dialogue: Flying is for droids.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) I'm hit! Anakin?
Dialogue: I'm hit! Anakin?

Script: ANAKIN: I see them . . . Buzz Droids.
Dialogue: I see them . . . Buzz Droids.

Script: OBI-WAN: Arfour be careful. You have one . . .
Dialogue: Arfour be careful. You have one . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Oh dear. They're shutting down all the controls.
Dialogue: Oh dear. They're shutting down all the controls.

Script: ANAKIN: Move to the right so I can get a clear shot at them.
Dialogue: Move to the right so I can get a clear shot at them.

Script: OBI-WAN: The mission. Get to the Command Ship. Get the Chancellor! I'm running out of tricks here.
Dialogue: The mission. Get to the Command Ship. Get the Chancellor! I'm running out of tricks here.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) In the name of ...
Dialogue: In the name of ...

Script: ANAKIN: Steady . . . steady . . .
Dialogue: Steady . . . steady . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin hold your fire . . . hold your fire. You're not helping here.
Dialogue: Anakin hold your fire . . . hold your fire. You're not helping here.

Script: ANAKIN: I agree bad idea. Swing right . . . ease over . . . steady . . .
Dialogue: I agree bad idea. Swing right . . . ease over . . . steady . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Wait . . . wait . . . I can't see a thing! My cockpit's fogging. They're all over me Anakin.
Dialogue: Wait . . . wait . . . I can't see a thing! My cockpit's fogging. They're all over me Anakin.

Script: ANAKIN: Move to the right.
Dialogue: Move to the right.

Script: OBI-WAN: Hold on Anakin. You're going to get us both killed! Get out of here. There's nothing more you can do.
Dialogue: Hold on Anakin. You're going to get us both killed! Get out of here. There's nothing more you can do.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm not leaving without you Master.
Dialogue: I'm not leaving without you Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: Blast it ... I can't see . . . my controls are gone.
Dialogue: Blast it ... I can't see . . . my controls are gone.

Script: ANAKIN: Get 'em Artoo. Watch out!
Dialogue: Get 'em Artoo. Watch out!

Script: OBI-WAN: Artoo hit the buzz droid's center eye.
Dialogue: Artoo hit the buzz droid's center eye.

Script: ANAKIN: Yeah you got him!
Dialogue: Yeah you got him!

Script: OBI-WAN: Great Artoo.
Dialogue: Great Artoo.

Script: ANAKIN: Stay on my wing . . . the General's Command Ship is dead ahead. Easy . . . pull up ... Head for the hangar.
Dialogue: Stay on my wing . . . the General's Command Ship is dead ahead. Easy . . . pull up ... Head for the hangar.

Script: OBI-WAN: Have you noticed the shields are still up?
Dialogue: Have you noticed the shields are still up?

Script: ANAKIN: Oh?!? Sorry Master.
Dialogue: Oh?!? Sorry Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: Oh I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: Oh I have a bad feeling about this.

Script: OBI-WAN: Artoo locate the Chancellor.
Dialogue: Artoo locate the Chancellor.

Script: ANAKIN: Tap into the ship's computers.
Dialogue: Tap into the ship's computers.

Script: OBI-WAN: The Chancellor's signal is coming from right there. The observation platform at the top of that spire.
Dialogue: The Chancellor's signal is coming from right there. The observation platform at the top of that spire.

Script: ANAKIN: I sense Count Dooku . . .
Dialogue: I sense Count Dooku . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: I sense a trap.
Dialogue: I sense a trap.

Script: ANAKIN: Next move?
Dialogue: Next move?

Script: OBI-WAN: Spring the trap.
Dialogue: Spring the trap.

Script: ANAKIN: Artoo go back. I need you to stay with the ship.
Dialogue: Artoo go back. I need you to stay with the ship.

Script: OBI-WAN: Here take this and wait for orders.
Dialogue: Here take this and wait for orders.

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: What's the situation Captain?
Dialogue: What's the situation Captain?

Script: CAPTAIN: TWO Jedi have landed in the main hangar bay.
Dialogue: TWO Jedi have landed in the main hangar bay.

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Just as Count Dooku predicted.
Dialogue: Just as Count Dooku predicted.

Script: BODYGUARD I: General Kenobi Anakin Skywalker. We've been waiting for you.
Dialogue: General Kenobi Anakin Skywalker. We've been waiting for you.

Script: OBI-WAN: We are here to relieve you of Chancellor Palpatine not join him.
Dialogue: We are here to relieve you of Chancellor Palpatine not join him.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin. . .
Dialogue: Anakin. . .

Script: ANAKIN: Ready.
Dialogue: Ready.

Script: OBI-WAN: . . . fuel. The slightest charge from our sabers will send this ship into oblivion. That's why they've stopped shooting.
Dialogue: . . . fuel. The slightest charge from our sabers will send this ship into oblivion. That's why they've stopped shooting.

Script: ANAKIN: Well then we're safe for the time being.
Dialogue: Well then we're safe for the time being.

Script: OBI-WAN: Your idea of safe is not the same as mine.
Dialogue: Your idea of safe is not the same as mine.

Script: ANAKIN: They're sealing this section off.
Dialogue: They're sealing this section off.

Script: OBI-WAN: Six droids coming our way!
Dialogue: Six droids coming our way!

Script: ANAKIN: Keep moving. There must be vents . . . This way.
Dialogue: Keep moving. There must be vents . . . This way.

Script: OBI-WAN: We'll never get through that. It's too small!
Dialogue: We'll never get through that. It's too small!

Script: ANAKIN: I found our escape vent.
Dialogue: I found our escape vent.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin this is no time for jokes. We're in serious trouble here.
Dialogue: Anakin this is no time for jokes. We're in serious trouble here.

Script: ANAKIN: Only in your mind. My Master. Look no structure. . . .
Dialogue: Only in your mind. My Master. Look no structure. . . .

Script: ANAKIN: Here's a way out.
Dialogue: Here's a way out.

Script: OBI-WAN: That won't hold when the fuel hits those power dischargers.
Dialogue: That won't hold when the fuel hits those power dischargers.

Script: ANAKIN: The blast will break the hull. This side's pressurized.
Dialogue: The blast will break the hull. This side's pressurized.

Script: OBI-WAN: You still have much to learn Anakin.
Dialogue: You still have much to learn Anakin.

Script: SUPER BATTLE DROID R77: I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: I have a bad feeling about this.

Script: OBI-WAN: All right you win. I have much to learn. Let's go!
Dialogue: All right you win. I have much to learn. Let's go!

Script: ANAKIN: Destroyers!!
Dialogue: Destroyers!!

Script: BATTLE DROID: Drop your weapons! I said drop 'em.
Dialogue: Drop your weapons! I said drop 'em.

Script: OBI-WAN: Did you press the stop button?
Dialogue: Did you press the stop button?

Script: ANAKIN: No did you?
Dialogue: No did you?

Script: OBI-WAN: No!
Dialogue: No!

Script: ANAKIN: Well there's more than one way out of here.
Dialogue: Well there's more than one way out of here.

Script: OBI-WAN: We don't want to get out we want to get moving. Artoo . . . Artoo. Do you copy? Activate elevator . . . (looks at control panel) . . . 31174 . . .
