Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) Yeah! We got him . . . good going Artoo.
Dialogue: Yeah! We got him . . . good going Artoo.

Script: OBI-WAN: Next time you're the bait . . . Now let's find the Command Ship and get on with it ...
Dialogue: Next time you're the bait . . . Now let's find the Command Ship and get on with it ...

Script: ANAKIN: Lock onto them Artoo. Master General Grievous's ship is directly ahead.
Dialogue: Lock onto them Artoo. Master General Grievous's ship is directly ahead.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) The one crawling with vulture droids.
Dialogue: The one crawling with vulture droids.

Script: OBI-WAN: I see it. Oh this is going to be easy.
Dialogue: I see it. Oh this is going to be easy.

Script: ANAKIN: Come on Master.
Dialogue: Come on Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: Not this time. There's too much at stake. We need help. Odd Ball do you copy?
Dialogue: Not this time. There's too much at stake. We need help. Odd Ball do you copy?

Script: ODD BALL: (OS) Copy Red Leader.
Dialogue: Copy Red Leader.

Script: OBI-WAN: Mark my position and form your squad up behind me . . .
Dialogue: Mark my position and form your squad up behind me . . .

Script: ODD BALL: We're on your tail General Kenobi. Set S-foils in attack position.
Dialogue: We're on your tail General Kenobi. Set S-foils in attack position.

Dialogue: I know. I know!

Dialogue: Too dangerous. First Jedi rule: "Survive."

Dialogue: Just keep me steady . . . hold on ... not yet. . . now break left.

Dialogue: You'll never get through there Anakin. It's too tight.

Dialogue: Easy Artoo . . . we've done this before.

Dialogue: Use the Force think yourself through the ship will follow.

Dialogue: I'm through.

Dialogue: There are too many of them.

Dialogue: I'm on your wing. Break left. Break left. They're all over me. Get them off my . . .

Dialogue: I'm going to go help them out!

Dialogue: No no! They are doing their job so we can do ours. Head for the Command Ship!

Dialogue: Missiles! Pull up!

Dialogue: They're coming around!

Dialogue: We got 'em. Artoo!

Dialogue: I'm hit! Anakin?

Dialogue: Move to the right so I can get a clear shot at them.

Dialogue: The mission. Get to the Command Ship. Get the Chancellor! I'm running out of tricks here.

Dialogue: In the name of ...

Dialogue: Steady . . . steady . . .

Dialogue: Anakin hold your fire . . . hold your fire. You're not helping here.

Dialogue: I agree bad idea. Swing right . . . ease over . . . steady . . .

Dialogue: Wait . . . wait . . . I can't see a thing! My cockpit's fogging. They're all over me Anakin.

Dialogue: Move to the right.

Dialogue: Hold on Anakin. You're going to get us both killed! Get out of here. There's nothing more you can do.

Dialogue: Yeah you got him!

Dialogue: Have you noticed the shields are still up?

Dialogue: Oh I have a bad feeling about this.

Dialogue: Artoo locate the Chancellor.

Dialogue: Tap into the ship's computers.

Dialogue: The Chancellor's signal is coming from right there. The observation platform at the top of that spire.

Dialogue: I sense Count Dooku . . .

Dialogue: What's the situation Captain?

Dialogue: Just as Count Dooku predicted.

Dialogue: General Kenobi Anakin Skywalker. We've been waiting for you.

Dialogue: We are here to relieve you of Chancellor Palpatine not join him.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin. . .
Dialogue: Anakin. . .

Script: ANAKIN: Ready.
Dialogue: Ready.

Dialogue: . . . fuel. The slightest charge from our sabers will send this ship into oblivion. That's why they've stopped shooting.

Dialogue: Well then we're safe for the time being.

Script: OBI-WAN: Your idea of safe is not the same as mine.
Dialogue: Your idea of safe is not the same as mine.

Dialogue: They're sealing this section off.

Dialogue: Six droids coming our way!

Dialogue: We'll never get through that. It's too small!

Script: ANAKIN: I found our escape vent.
Dialogue: I found our escape vent.

Dialogue: Only in your mind. My Master. Look no structure. . . .

Dialogue: Here's a way out.

Dialogue: That won't hold when the fuel hits those power dischargers.

Dialogue: The blast will break the hull. This side's pressurized.

Script: OBI-WAN: You still have much to learn Anakin.
Dialogue: You still have much to learn Anakin.

Dialogue: I have a bad feeling about this.

Script: OBI-WAN: All right you win. I have much to learn. Let's go!

Dialogue: Artoo switch on the comlink. Artoo do you hear me? Artoo we gave you a job to do! Artoo.

Dialogue: Artoo do you copy? Artoo do you hear me? Artoo we need to be going up not down.

Dialogue: You stupid little astro droid!

Dialogue: Your swords please Master Jedi. We don't want to make a mess of things in front of the Chancellor.

Dialogue: You won't get away this time Dooku.

Dialogue: I've been looking forward to this.

Dialogue: Good. Twice the pride double the fall.

Dialogue: Your moves are clumsy Kenobi . . . too predictable. You'll have to do better.

Dialogue: I sense great fear in you Skywalker. You have hate you have anger but you dont use them.

Dialogue: Good Anakin good. I knew you could do it. Kill him. Kill him now!

Dialogue: I shouldn't . . .

Script: PALPATINE: Do it!!
Dialogue: Do it!!

Script: ANAKIN: ... I couldn't stop myself.
Dialogue: ... I couldn't stop myself.

Dialogue: You did well Anakin. He was too dangerous to be kept alive.

Dialogue: Yes but he was an unarmed prisoner.

Dialogue: I shouldn't have done that Chancellor. It's not the Jedi way.

Dialogue: Anakin there is no time. We must get off the ship before it's too late.

Dialogue: He seems to be all right. No broken bones breathing's all right.

Dialogue: Leave him or we'll never make it.

Script: ANAKIN: His fate will be the same as ours.
Dialogue: His fate will be the same as ours.

Dialogue: All batteries fire! Fire!

Dialogue: Artoo ... do you copy? Artoo come in!

Dialogue: Magnetize! Magnetize!

Dialogue: We can't wait. Come on we have to be fast.

Dialogue: Fire the emergency booster engines.

Script: PILOT: Leveling out sir.
Dialogue: Leveling out sir.

Dialogue: Easy. . . . We're in a bit of a situation.

Dialogue: Did I miss something?

Script: ANAKINN: Hold on.
Dialogue: Hold on.

Script: OBI-WAN: What is that?
Dialogue: What is that?

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) Oops.
Dialogue: Oops.

Dialogue: Artoo Artoo shut down the elevator!

Dialogue: Too late! Jump!

Script: OBI-WAN:  of those ships will get us anywhere.
Dialogue: of those ships will get us anywhere.

Dialogue: I agree.

Dialogue: What are we going to do?

Script: ANAKIN: I don't know.
Dialogue: I don't know.

Script: OBI-WAN: Don't look at me. I don't know.
Dialogue: Don't look at me. I don't know.

Dialogue: Here Chancellor lock this around your waist and hold on.

Dialogue: We'll head toward the bridge and see if we can find an escape pod.

Script: ANAKIN/OBI-WAN: Well that was close.
Dialogue: Well that was close.

Dialogue: General we found the Jedi. They're in hallway 328.

Dialogue: Activate ray shields.

Script: ANAKIN: Ray shields!
Dialogue: Ray shields!

Script: OBI-WAN: Wait a minute how'd this happen! We're smarter than this.
Dialogue: Wait a minute how'd this happen! We're smarter than this.

Script: ANAKIN: Apparently not Master. This is the oldest trap in the book . . . Well ... I was distracted.
Dialogue: Apparently not Master. This is the oldest trap in the book . . . Well ... I was distracted.

Script: OBI-WAN: Oh so all of a sudden it's my fault.
Dialogue: Oh so all of a sudden it's my fault.

Script: ANAKIN: You're the Master. I'm just a hero.
Dialogue: You're the Master. I'm just a hero.

Script: OBI-WAN: I'm open to suggestions here.
Dialogue: I'm open to suggestions here.

Script: PALPATINE: Why don't we let them take us to General Grievous. Perhaps with Count Dooku's demise we can negotiate our release.
Dialogue: Why don't we let them take us to General Grievous. Perhaps with Count Dooku's demise we can negotiate our release.

Script: ANAKIN: I say . . . patience.
Dialogue: I say . . . patience.

Dialogue: Patience! That's your plan is it?

Script: ANAKIN: Yes Artoo will be along in a few moments and he'll release the ray shields . . .
Dialogue: Yes Artoo will be along in a few moments and he'll release the ray shields . . .

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) See! No problem.
Dialogue: See! No problem.

Dialogue: Do you have a plan B?

Dialogue: Oh yes. General Kenobi the Negotiator. We've been waiting for you. That wasn't much of a rescue.

Dialogue: That depends upon your point of view. Hah!

Dialogue: And Anakin Skywalker ... I was expecting someone with your reputation to be a little older.

Script: ANAKIN: General Grievous . . . Supreme Commander of the Droid Armies. You're shorter than I expected.
Dialogue: General Grievous . . . Supreme Commander of the Droid Armies. You're shorter than I expected.

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Ahhhh Jedi scum . . .
Dialogue: Ahhhh Jedi scum . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin try not to upset him. We have a job to do.
Dialogue: Anakin try not to upset him. We have a job to do.

Dialogue: Your lightsabers will make a fine addition to my collection.

Dialogue: Not this time. And this time you won't escape.

Script: ANAKIN: Artoo.
Dialogue: Artoo.

Dialogue: Crush them! Make them suffer!

Dialogue: Stay on course . . . Don't bother with them. Keep the ship in orbit.

Dialogue: You mean do I know how to land what's left of this thing?

Script: OBI-WAN: Well?
Dialogue: Well?

Script: ANAKIN: Under the circumstances I'd say the ability to pilot this thing is irrelevant. Strap yourselves in.
Dialogue: Under the circumstances I'd say the ability to pilot this thing is irrelevant. Strap yourselves in.

Script: OBI-WAN: Steady . . . Attitude . . . eighteen degrees.
Dialogue: Steady . . . Attitude . . . eighteen degrees.

Script: ANAKIN: Pressure rising. We've got to slow this wreck down. Open all hatches extend all flaps and drag fins.
Dialogue: Pressure rising. We've got to slow this wreck down. Open all hatches extend all flaps and drag fins.

Script: OBI-WAN: Temp steady. Hatches open flaps extended drag fins . . .
Dialogue: Temp steady. Hatches open flaps extended drag fins . . .

Script: ANAKIN: We lost something.
Dialogue: We lost something.

Script: OBI-WAN: Not to worry we're still flying half the ship.
Dialogue: Not to worry we're still flying half the ship.

Script: ANAKIN: Now we're really picking up speed . . . I'm going to shift a few degrees and see if I can slow us down.
Dialogue: Now we're really picking up speed . . . I'm going to shift a few degrees and see if I can slow us down.

Script: OBI-WAN: Careful . . . we're heating up-twelve thousand . . . thirteen thousand . . .
Dialogue: Careful . . . we're heating up-twelve thousand . . . thirteen thousand . . .

Script: ANAKIN: What's our speed?
Dialogue: What's our speed?

Script: OBI-WAN: Eight plus sixty-forty. Eight plus sixty-twenty. Eight plus sixty. Temp ten thousand nine thousand . . . we're in the atmosphere . . .
Dialogue: Eight plus sixty-forty. Eight plus sixty-twenty. Eight plus sixty. Temp ten thousand nine thousand . . . we're in the atmosphere . . .

Script: ANAKIN: Grab that . . . Keep us level.
Dialogue: Grab that . . . Keep us level.

Script: OBI-WAN: Steady. Steady.
Dialogue: Steady. Steady.

Script: ANAKIN: Easy Artoo. Hang on this may get a little rough. We lost our heat shields.
Dialogue: Easy Artoo. Hang on this may get a little rough. We lost our heat shields.

Script: OBI-WAN: Five thousand. Three thousand . . . two thousand. Fireships on the left and the right.
Dialogue: Five thousand. Three thousand . . . two thousand. Fireships on the left and the right.

Script: FlRESHIP PILOT: We'll take you in.
Dialogue: We'll take you in.

Script: OBI-WAN: Copy that. Landing strip's straight ahead.
Dialogue: Copy that. Landing strip's straight ahead.

Script: ANAKIN: We're coming in too hot.
Dialogue: We're coming in too hot.

Script: OBI-WAN: Easy-easy.
Dialogue: Easy-easy.

Script: OBI-WAN: Another happy landing.
Dialogue: Another happy landing.

Script: ANAKIN: (to Obi-Wan) Are you coming Master?
Dialogue: Are you coming Master?

Script: OBI-WAN: Oh no. I'm not brave enough for politics. I have to report to the Council. Besides someone needs to be the poster boy.
Dialogue: Oh no. I'm not brave enough for politics. I have to report to the Council. Besides someone needs to be the poster boy.

Script: ANAKIN: Hold on this whole operation was your idea. You planned it. You led the rescue operation. You have to be the one to take the bows this time.
Dialogue: Hold on this whole operation was your idea. You planned it. You led the rescue operation. You have to be the one to take the bows this time.

Script: OBI-WAN: Sorry old friend. Let us not forget that you rescued me from the Buzz Droids. And you killed Count Dooku. And you rescued the Chancellor carrying me unconscious on your back and you managed to land that bucket of bolts safely . . .
Dialogue: Sorry old friend. Let us not forget that you rescued me from the Buzz Droids. And you killed Count Dooku. And you rescued the Chancellor carrying me unconscious on your back and you managed to land that bucket of bolts safely . . .

Script: ANAKIN: All because of your training Master. You deserve all those speeches of your greatness.
Dialogue: All because of your training Master. You deserve all those speeches of your greatness.

Script: OBI-WAN: . . . the endless speeches . . . Anakin let's be fair. Today you are the hero and you deserve your glorious day with the politicians.
Dialogue: . . . the endless speeches . . . Anakin let's be fair. Today you are the hero and you deserve your glorious day with the politicians.

Script: ANAKIN: All right. But you owe me . . . and not for saving your skin for the tenth time . . .
Dialogue: All right. But you owe me . . . and not for saving your skin for the tenth time . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: Ninth time . . . that business on Cato Nemoidia doesn't count. I'll see you at the briefing.
Dialogue: Ninth time . . . that business on Cato Nemoidia doesn't count. I'll see you at the briefing.

Script: MACE WlNDU: Chancellor Palpatine what a welcome sight! Are you all right?
Dialogue: Chancellor Palpatine what a welcome sight! Are you all right?

Script: PALPATINE: Yes thanks to your two Jedi Knights. They killed Count Dooku but General Grievous has escaped once again.
Dialogue: Yes thanks to your two Jedi Knights. They killed Count Dooku but General Grievous has escaped once again.

Script: MACE WlNDU: General Grievous will run and hide as he always does. He is a coward.
Dialogue: General Grievous will run and hide as he always does. He is a coward.

Script: PALPATINE: That maybe true but with Count Dooku dead he is the leader of the Droid Army and I assure you the Senate will vote to continue the war as long as Grievous is alive.
Dialogue: That maybe true but with Count Dooku dead he is the leader of the Droid Army and I assure you the Senate will vote to continue the war as long as Grievous is alive.

Script: MACE WlNDU: Then the Jedi Council will make finding Grievous our highest priority.
Dialogue: Then the Jedi Council will make finding Grievous our highest priority.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Skywalker the Republic cannot praise you enough.
Dialogue: Skywalker the Republic cannot praise you enough.

Script: ANAKIN: Thank you Senator Organa. The kidnapping was a bold move by the Separatists but it was a mistake that Obi-Wan and I were able to take advantage of.
Dialogue: Thank you Senator Organa. The kidnapping was a bold move by the Separatists but it was a mistake that Obi-Wan and I were able to take advantage of.

Script: C-3PO: It couldn't possibly be as bad as all that.
Dialogue: It couldn't possibly be as bad as all that.

Script: C-3PO: (continuing) Well there I agree with you. In fact I could do with a tune-up myself.
Dialogue: Well there I agree with you. In fact I could do with a tune-up myself.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: The end of Count Dooku will surely bring an end to this war and an end to the Chancellor's draconian security measures.
Dialogue: The end of Count Dooku will surely bring an end to this war and an end to the Chancellor's draconian security measures.

Script: ANAKIN: I wish that were so but the fighting is going to continue until General Grievous is spare parts . . . The Chancellor is very clear about that.
Dialogue: I wish that were so but the fighting is going to continue until General Grievous is spare parts . . . The Chancellor is very clear about that.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: I'll do everything I can with the Senate.
Dialogue: I'll do everything I can with the Senate.

Script: ANAKIN: Excuse me.
Dialogue: Excuse me.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Certainly.
Dialogue: Certainly.

Script: PADME: Oh Anakin! Thank goodness you're back.
Dialogue: Oh Anakin! Thank goodness you're back.

Script: ANAKIN: I missed you Padme. I've missed you so.
Dialogue: I missed you Padme. I've missed you so.

Script: PADME: There were whispers . . . that you'd been killed. I've been living with unbearable dread.
Dialogue: There were whispers . . . that you'd been killed. I've been living with unbearable dread.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm back I'm all right. It feels like we've been apart for a lifetime. And it might have been ... If the Chancellor hadn't been kidnapped. I don't think they would have ever brought us back from the Outer Rim sieges.
Dialogue: I'm back I'm all right. It feels like we've been apart for a lifetime. And it might have been ... If the Chancellor hadn't been kidnapped. I don't think they would have ever brought us back from the Outer Rim sieges.

Script: PADME: Wait not here . . .
Dialogue: Wait not here . . .

Script: ANAKIN: Yes here! I'm tired of all this deception. I don't care if they know we're married.
Dialogue: Yes here! I'm tired of all this deception. I don't care if they know we're married.

Script: PADME: Anakin don't say things like that. You're important to the Republic ... to ending this war. I love you more than anything but I won't let you give up your life as a Jedi for me . . .
Dialogue: Anakin don't say things like that. You're important to the Republic ... to ending this war. I love you more than anything but I won't let you give up your life as a Jedi for me . . .

Script: ANAKIN: I've given my life to the Jedi order but I'd only give up my life for you.
Dialogue: I've given my life to the Jedi order but I'd only give up my life for you.

Script: PADME: (playfully) I wouldn't like that. I wouldn't like that one bit. Patience my handsome Jedi . . . Come to me later.
Dialogue: I wouldn't like that. I wouldn't like that one bit. Patience my handsome Jedi . . . Come to me later.

Script: ANAKIN: Are you all right? You're trembling. What's going on?
Dialogue: Are you all right? You're trembling. What's going on?

Script: PADME: I'm just excited to see you.
Dialogue: I'm just excited to see you.

Script: ANAKIN: That's not it. I sense more . . . what is it?
Dialogue: That's not it. I sense more . . . what is it?

Script: PADME: Nothing . . . nothing . . .
Dialogue: Nothing . . . nothing . . .

Script: ANAKIN: You're frightened. (a little angry) Tell me what's going on!
Dialogue: You're frightened.  Tell me what's going on!

Script: PADME: You've been gone five months . . . it's been very hard for me. I've never felt so alone. There's . . .
Dialogue: You've been gone five months . . . it's been very hard for me. I've never felt so alone. There's . . .

Script: ANAKIN: . . . Is there someone else?
Dialogue: . . . Is there someone else?

Script: PADME: (peeved angry) No! Why do you think that? Your jealousy upsets me so much Anakin. I do nothing to betray you yet you still don't trust me. Nothing has changed.
Dialogue: No! Why do you think that? Your jealousy upsets me so much Anakin. I do nothing to betray you yet you still don't trust me. Nothing has changed.

Script: ANAKIN: (sheepish) I'm afraid of losing you Padme . . . that's all.
Dialogue: I'm afraid of losing you Padme . . . that's all.

Script: PADME: I will never stop loving you Anakin. My only fear is losing you.
Dialogue: I will never stop loving you Anakin. My only fear is losing you.

Script: ANAKIN: It's just that I've never seen you like this . . .
Dialogue: It's just that I've never seen you like this . . .

Script: PADME: Something wonderful has happened.
Dialogue: Something wonderful has happened.

Script: PADME: (continuing) I'm . . . Annie I'm pregnant.
Dialogue: I'm . . . Annie I'm pregnant.

Script: ANAKIN: That's . . . that's wonderful.
Dialogue: That's . . . that's wonderful.

Script: PADME: What are we going to do?
Dialogue: What are we going to do?

Script: ANAKIN: We're not going to worry about anything right now all right? This is a happy moment. The happiest moment of my life.
Dialogue: We're not going to worry about anything right now all right? This is a happy moment. The happiest moment of my life.

Script: SUPER BATTLE DROID G21: The planet is secure sir. The population is under control.
Dialogue: The planet is secure sir. The population is under control.

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Good. Where is the Separatist Council?
Dialogue: Good. Where is the Separatist Council?

Script: SUPER BATTLE DROID G21: This way sir ...
Dialogue: This way sir ...

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: Yes Lord Sidious.
Dialogue: Yes Lord Sidious.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: General Grievous I suggest you move the Separatist leaders to Mustafar.
Dialogue: General Grievous I suggest you move the Separatist leaders to Mustafar.

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: It will be done My Lord.
Dialogue: It will be done My Lord.

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: The end of the war is near General and I promise you victory is assured.
Dialogue: The end of the war is near General and I promise you victory is assured.

Script: GENERAL GRIEVOUS: But the loss of Count Dooku?
Dialogue: But the loss of Count Dooku?

Script: DARTH SlDIOUS: His death was a necessary loss which will ensure our victory. Soon I will have a new apprentice . . . one far younger and more powerful than Lord Tyranus.
Dialogue: His death was a necessary loss which will ensure our victory. Soon I will have a new apprentice . . . one far younger and more powerful than Lord Tyranus.

Script: ANAKIN: . . . every second I was thinking of you. Protecting the endless nameless Outer Rim settlements became a torture . . . the battles were easy the longing became unbearable . . . I've never been so happy as I am at this moment.
Dialogue: . . . every second I was thinking of you. Protecting the endless nameless Outer Rim settlements became a torture . . . the battles were easy the longing became unbearable . . . I've never been so happy as I am at this moment.

Script: PADME: Annie I want to have our baby back home on Naboo. We could go to the lake country where no one would know . . . where we would be safe. I could go early-and fix up the baby's room. I know the perfect spot right by the gardens.
Dialogue: Annie I want to have our baby back home on Naboo. We could go to the lake country where no one would know . . . where we would be safe. I could go early-and fix up the baby's room. I know the perfect spot right by the gardens.

Script: ANAKIN: You are so beautiful!
Dialogue: You are so beautiful!

Script: PADME: It's only because I'm so in love . . .
Dialogue: It's only because I'm so in love . . .

Script: ANAKIN: No it's because I'm so in love with you.
Dialogue: No it's because I'm so in love with you.

Script: PADME: So love has blinded you?
Dialogue: So love has blinded you?

Script: ANAKIN: Well that's not exactly what I meant . . .
Dialogue: Well that's not exactly what I meant . . .

Script: PADME: But it's probably true!
Dialogue: But it's probably true!

Script: ANAKIN: I haven't laughed in so long . . .
Dialogue: I haven't laughed in so long . . .

Script: PADME: Neither have I.
Dialogue: Neither have I.

Script: PADME: Anakin help me! Help Anakin! Anakin I love you. I love you.
Dialogue: Anakin help me! Help Anakin! Anakin I love you. I love you.

Script: PADME: Anakin??
Dialogue: Anakin??

Script: PADME: What's bothering you?
Dialogue: What's bothering you?

Script: ANAKIN: Nothing . . .
Dialogue: Nothing . . .

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) I remember when I gave this to you.
Dialogue: I remember when I gave this to you.

Script: PADME: Anakin how long is it going to take for us to be honest with each other?
Dialogue: Anakin how long is it going to take for us to be honest with each other?

Script: ANAKIN: It was a dream.
Dialogue: It was a dream.

Script: PADME: Bad?
Dialogue: Bad?

Script: ANAKIN: Like the ones I used to have about my mother just before she died.
Dialogue: Like the ones I used to have about my mother just before she died.

Script: PADME: And?
Dialogue: And?

Script: ANAKIN: It was about you.
Dialogue: It was about you.

Script: PADME: Tell me.
Dialogue: Tell me.

Script: ANAKIN: It was only a dream.
Dialogue: It was only a dream.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) You die in childbirth . . .
Dialogue: You die in childbirth . . .

Script: PADME: And the baby?
Dialogue: And the baby?

Script: ANAKIN: I don't know.
Dialogue: I don't know.

Script: PADME: It was only a dream.
Dialogue: It was only a dream.

Script: ANAKIN: . . . I won't let this one become real Padme.
Dialogue: . . . I won't let this one become real Padme.

Script: PADME: Anakin this baby will change our lives. I doubt the Queen will continue to allow me to serve in the Senate and if the Council discovers you are the father you will be expelled from the Jedi Order.
Dialogue: Anakin this baby will change our lives. I doubt the Queen will continue to allow me to serve in the Senate and if the Council discovers you are the father you will be expelled from the Jedi Order.

Script: ANAKIN: I know .
Dialogue: I know .

Script: PADME: Anakin do you think Obi-Wan might be able to help us?
Dialogue: Anakin do you think Obi-Wan might be able to help us?

Script: ANAKIN: (suspicious) Have you told him anything?
Dialogue: Have you told him anything?

Script: PADME: No but he's your mentor your best friend . . . he must suspect something.
Dialogue: No but he's your mentor your best friend . . . he must suspect something.

Script: ANAKIN: He's been a father to me but he's still on the Council. Don't tell him anything!
Dialogue: He's been a father to me but he's still on the Council. Don't tell him anything!

Script: PADME: I won't Anakin.
Dialogue: I won't Anakin.

Script: ANAKIN: I don't need his help . . . Our baby is a blessing not a problem.
Dialogue: I don't need his help . . . Our baby is a blessing not a problem.

Script: YODA: Premonitions . . . premonitions . . . Hmmmm . . . these visions you have . . .
Dialogue: Premonitions . . . premonitions . . . Hmmmm . . . these visions you have . . .

Script: ANAKIN: They are of pain suffering death . . .
Dialogue: They are of pain suffering death . . .

Script: YODA: Yourself you speak of or someone you know?
Dialogue: Yourself you speak of or someone you know?

Script: ANAKIN: Someone . . .
Dialogue: Someone . . .

Script: YODA: . . . close to you?
Dialogue: . . . close to you?

Script: ANAKIN: Yes.
Dialogue: Yes.

Script: YODA: Careful you must be when sensing the future Anakin. The fear of loss is a path to the dark side.
Dialogue: Careful you must be when sensing the future Anakin. The fear of loss is a path to the dark side.

Script: ANAKIN: I won't let these visions come true Master Yoda.
Dialogue: I won't let these visions come true Master Yoda.

Script: YODA: Death is a natural part of life. Rejoice for those around you who transform into the Force. Mourn them do not. Miss them do not. Attachment leads to jealousy. The shadow of greed that is.
Dialogue: Death is a natural part of life. Rejoice for those around you who transform into the Force. Mourn them do not. Miss them do not. Attachment leads to jealousy. The shadow of greed that is.

Script: ANAKIN: What must I do Master Yoda?
Dialogue: What must I do Master Yoda?

Script: YODA: Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.
Dialogue: Train yourself to let go of everything you fear to lose.

Script: OBI-WAN: You missed the report on the Outer Rim sieges.
Dialogue: You missed the report on the Outer Rim sieges.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm sorry I was held up. I have no excuse.
Dialogue: I'm sorry I was held up. I have no excuse.

Script: OBI-WAN: In short they are going very well. Saleucami has fallen and Master Vos has moved his troops to Boz Pity.
Dialogue: In short they are going very well. Saleucami has fallen and Master Vos has moved his troops to Boz Pity.

Script: ANAKIN: What's wrong then?
Dialogue: What's wrong then?

Script: OBI-WAN: The Senate is expected to vote more executive powers to the Chancellor today.
Dialogue: The Senate is expected to vote more executive powers to the Chancellor today.

Script: ANAKIN: Well that can only mean less deliberating and more action. Is that bad? It will make it easier for us to end this war.
Dialogue: Well that can only mean less deliberating and more action. Is that bad? It will make it easier for us to end this war.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin be careful of your friend Palpatine.
Dialogue: Anakin be careful of your friend Palpatine.

Script: ANAKIN: Be careful of what?
Dialogue: Be careful of what?

Script: OBI-WAN: He has requested your presence.
Dialogue: He has requested your presence.

Script: ANAKIN: What for?
Dialogue: What for?

Script: OBI-WAN: He would not say.
Dialogue: He would not say.

Script: ANAKIN: He didn't inform the Jedi Council? That's unusual isn't it?
Dialogue: He didn't inform the Jedi Council? That's unusual isn't it?

Script: OBI-WAN: All of this is unusual and it's making me feel uneasy. You're probably aware that relations between the Council and the Chancellor are stressed.
Dialogue: All of this is unusual and it's making me feel uneasy. You're probably aware that relations between the Council and the Chancellor are stressed.

Script: ANAKIN: I know the Council has grown wary of the Chancellor's power mine also for that matter. Aren't we all working together to save the Republic? Why all this distrust?
Dialogue: I know the Council has grown wary of the Chancellor's power mine also for that matter. Aren't we all working together to save the Republic? Why all this distrust?

Script: OBI-WAN: The Force grows dark Anakin and we are all affected by it. Be wary of your feelings.
Dialogue: The Force grows dark Anakin and we are all affected by it. Be wary of your feelings.

Script: PALPATINE: Anakin this afternoon the Senate is going to call on me to take direct control of the Jedi Council.
Dialogue: Anakin this afternoon the Senate is going to call on me to take direct control of the Jedi Council.

Script: ANAKIN: The Jedi will no longer report to the Senate?
Dialogue: The Jedi will no longer report to the Senate?

Script: PALPATINE: They will report to me . . . personally. The Senate is too unfocused to conduct a war. This will bring a quick end to things.
Dialogue: They will report to me . . . personally. The Senate is too unfocused to conduct a war. This will bring a quick end to things.

Script: ANAKIN: I agree but the Jedi Council may not see it that way.
Dialogue: I agree but the Jedi Council may not see it that way.

Script: PALPATINE: There are times when we must all endure adjustments to the constitution in the name of security.
Dialogue: There are times when we must all endure adjustments to the constitution in the name of security.

Script: ANAKIN: With all due respect sir the Council is in no mood for more constitutional amendments.
Dialogue: With all due respect sir the Council is in no mood for more constitutional amendments.

Script: PALPATINE: Thank you my friend but in this case I have no choice . . . this war must be won.
Dialogue: Thank you my friend but in this case I have no choice . . . this war must be won.

Script: ANAKIN: Everyone will agree on that.
Dialogue: Everyone will agree on that.

Script: PALPATINE: Anakin I've known you since you were a small boy. I have advised you over the years when I could ... I am very proud of your accomplishments. You have won many battles the Jedi Council thought were lost . . . and you saved my life. I hope you trust me Anakin.
Dialogue: Anakin I've known you since you were a small boy. I have advised you over the years when I could ... I am very proud of your accomplishments. You have won many battles the Jedi Council thought were lost . . . and you saved my life. I hope you trust me Anakin.

Script: ANAKIN: Of course.
Dialogue: Of course.

Script: PALPATINE: I need your help son.
Dialogue: I need your help son.

Script: ANAKIN: What do you mean?
Dialogue: What do you mean?

Script: PALPATINE: I fear the Jedi. The Council keeps pushing for more control. They're shrouded in secrecy and obsessed with maintaining their autonomy . . . ideals. I find simply incomprehensible in a democracy.
Dialogue: I fear the Jedi. The Council keeps pushing for more control. They're shrouded in secrecy and obsessed with maintaining their autonomy . . . ideals. I find simply incomprehensible in a democracy.

Script: ANAKIN: I can assure you that the Jedi are dedicated to the values of the Republic sir.
Dialogue: I can assure you that the Jedi are dedicated to the values of the Republic sir.

Script: PALPATINE: Nevertheless their actions will speak more loudly than their words. I'm depending on you.
Dialogue: Nevertheless their actions will speak more loudly than their words. I'm depending on you.

Script: ANAKIN: For what? I don't understand.
Dialogue: For what? I don't understand.

Script: PALPATINE: To be the eyes ears and voice of the Republic . . .
Dialogue: To be the eyes ears and voice of the Republic . . .

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) Anakin . . . I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.
Dialogue: Anakin . . . I'm appointing you to be my personal representative on the Jedi Council.

Script: ANAKIN: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed sir but the Council elects its own members. They will never accept this.
Dialogue: Me? A Master? I am overwhelmed sir but the Council elects its own members. They will never accept this.

Script: PALPATINE: I think they will . . . they need you more than you know.
Dialogue: I think they will . . . they need you more than you know.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Now that he has control of the Jedi Council the Chancellor has appointed Governors to oversee all star systems in the Republic.
Dialogue: Now that he has control of the Jedi Council the Chancellor has appointed Governors to oversee all star systems in the Republic.

Script: FANG ZAR: When did this happen?
Dialogue: When did this happen?

Script: BAIL ORGANA: The decree was posted this morning.
Dialogue: The decree was posted this morning.

Script: PADME: Do you think he will dismantle the Senate?
Dialogue: Do you think he will dismantle the Senate?

Script: MON MOTHMA: Why bother? As a practical matter the Senate no longer exists.
Dialogue: Why bother? As a practical matter the Senate no longer exists.

Script: GIDDEAN DANU: The constitution is in shreds. Amendment after amendment . . . executive directives sometimes a dozen in one day.
Dialogue: The constitution is in shreds. Amendment after amendment . . . executive directives sometimes a dozen in one day.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: We can't let a thousand years of democracy disappear without a fight.
Dialogue: We can't let a thousand years of democracy disappear without a fight.

Script: TERR TANEEL: What are you suggesting?
Dialogue: What are you suggesting?

Script: BAIL ORGANA: I apologize. I didn't mean to sound like a Separatist.
Dialogue: I apologize. I didn't mean to sound like a Separatist.

Script: MON MOTHMA: We are not Separatists trying to leave the Republic. We are loyalists trying to preserve democracy in the Republic.
Dialogue: We are not Separatists trying to leave the Republic. We are loyalists trying to preserve democracy in the Republic.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: It has become increasingly clear to many of us that the Chancellor has become an enemy of democracy.
Dialogue: It has become increasingly clear to many of us that the Chancellor has become an enemy of democracy.

Script: PADME: I can't believe it has come to this! Chancellor Palpatine is one of my oldest advisors. He served as my Ambassador when I was Queen.
Dialogue: I can't believe it has come to this! Chancellor Palpatine is one of my oldest advisors. He served as my Ambassador when I was Queen.

Script: GlDDEAN DANU: Senator I fear you underestimate the amount of corruption that has taken hold in the Senate.
Dialogue: Senator I fear you underestimate the amount of corruption that has taken hold in the Senate.

Script: MON MOTHMA: The Chancellor has played the Senators well. They know where the power lies and they will do whatever it takes to share in it. Palpatine has become a dictator and we have helped him to do it.
Dialogue: The Chancellor has played the Senators well. They know where the power lies and they will do whatever it takes to share in it. Palpatine has become a dictator and we have helped him to do it.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: We can't sit around debating any longer we have decided to do what we can to stop it. Senator Mon Mothma and I are putting together an organization . . .
Dialogue: We can't sit around debating any longer we have decided to do what we can to stop it. Senator Mon Mothma and I are putting together an organization . . .

Script: PADME: Say no more. Senator Organa. I understand. At this point it's better to leave some things unsaid.
Dialogue: Say no more. Senator Organa. I understand. At this point it's better to leave some things unsaid.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Yes. I agree and we must not discuss this with anyone without everyone in this group agreeing.
Dialogue: Yes. I agree and we must not discuss this with anyone without everyone in this group agreeing.

Script: MON MOTHMA: That means those closest to you . . . even family ... no one can be told.
Dialogue: That means those closest to you . . . even family ... no one can be told.

Script: PADME: Agreed.
Dialogue: Agreed.

Script: MACE: Anakin Skywalker we have approved your appointment to the Council as the Chancellor's personal representative.
Dialogue: Anakin Skywalker we have approved your appointment to the Council as the Chancellor's personal representative.

Script: ANAKIN: I will do my best to uphold the principles of the Jedi Order.
Dialogue: I will do my best to uphold the principles of the Jedi Order.

Script: YODA: Allow this appointment lightly the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.
Dialogue: Allow this appointment lightly the Council does not. Disturbing is this move by Chancellor Palpatine.

Script: ANAKIN: I understand.
Dialogue: I understand.

Script: MACE: You are on this Council but we do not grant you the rank of Master.
Dialogue: You are on this Council but we do not grant you the rank of Master.

Script: ANAKIN: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous it's unfair . . . I'm more powerful than any of you. How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?
Dialogue: What? ! How can you do this?? This is outrageous it's unfair . . . I'm more powerful than any of you. How can you be on the Council and not be a Master?

Script: MACE: Take a seat young Skywalker.
Dialogue: Take a seat young Skywalker.

Script: ANAKIN: Forgive me Master.
Dialogue: Forgive me Master.

Script: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic and have found no sign of General Grievous.
Dialogue: We have surveyed all systems in the Republic and have found no sign of General Grievous.

Script: YODA: Hiding in the Outer Rim Grievous is. The outlying systems you must sweep.
Dialogue: Hiding in the Outer Rim Grievous is. The outlying systems you must sweep.

Script: OBI-WAN: It may take some time . . . we do not have many ships to spare.
Dialogue: It may take some time . . . we do not have many ships to spare.

Script: MACE: We cannot take ships from the front line.
Dialogue: We cannot take ships from the front line.

Script: OBI-WAN: And yet it would be fatal for us to allow the droid armies to regroup.
Dialogue: And yet it would be fatal for us to allow the droid armies to regroup.

Script: YODA: Master Kenobi our spies contact you must and then wait.
Dialogue: Master Kenobi our spies contact you must and then wait.

Script: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?
Dialogue: What about the droid attack on the Wookiees?

Script: MACE: It is critical we send an attack group there immediately!
Dialogue: It is critical we send an attack group there immediately!

Script: OBI-WAN: He's right that is a system we cannot afford to lose. It's the main navigation route for the southwestern quadrant.
Dialogue: He's right that is a system we cannot afford to lose. It's the main navigation route for the southwestern quadrant.

Script: ANAKIN: I know that system well. It would take us little time to drive the droids off that planet.
Dialogue: I know that system well. It would take us little time to drive the droids off that planet.

Script: MACE: Skywalker your assignment is here with the Chancellor and Kenobi must find General Grievous.
Dialogue: Skywalker your assignment is here with the Chancellor and Kenobi must find General Grievous.

Script: YODA: Go I will. Good relations with the Wookiees I have.
Dialogue: Go I will. Good relations with the Wookiees I have.

Script: MACE: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.
Dialogue: It is settled then. Yoda will take a battalion of clones to reinforce the Wookiees on Kashyyyk. May the Force be with us all.

Script: ANAKIN: What kind of nonsense is this put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!
Dialogue: What kind of nonsense is this put me on the Council and not make me a Master!?? That's never been done in the history of the Jedi. It's insulting!

Script: OBI-WAN: Calm down Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age . . . It's never happened before. Listen to me Anakin. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.
Dialogue: Calm down Anakin. You have been given a great honor. To be on the Council at your age . . . It's never happened before. Listen to me Anakin. The fact of the matter is you're too close to the Chancellor. The Council doesn't like it when he interferes in Jedi affairs.

Script: ANAKIN: I swear to you I didn't ask to be put on the Council . . .
Dialogue: I swear to you I didn't ask to be put on the Council . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.
Dialogue: But it's what you wanted! Your friendship with Chancellor Palpatine seems to have paid off.

Script: ANAKIN: That has nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: That has nothing to do with this.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin regardless of how it happened you find yourself in a delicate situation.
Dialogue: Anakin regardless of how it happened you find yourself in a delicate situation.

Script: ANAKIN: You mean divided loyalties.
Dialogue: You mean divided loyalties.

Script: OBI-WAN: I warned you there was tension between the Council and the Chancellor. I was very clear. Why didn't you listen? You walked right into it.
Dialogue: I warned you there was tension between the Council and the Chancellor. I was very clear. Why didn't you listen? You walked right into it.

Script: ANAKIN: The Council is upset I'm the youngest to ever serve.
Dialogue: The Council is upset I'm the youngest to ever serve.

Script: OBI-WAN: No it is not. Anakin I worry when you speak of jealousy and pride. Those are not Jedi thoughts. They're dangerous dark thoughts.
Dialogue: No it is not. Anakin I worry when you speak of jealousy and pride. Those are not Jedi thoughts. They're dangerous dark thoughts.

Script: ANAKIN: Master you of all people should have confidence in my abilities. I know where my loyalties lie.
Dialogue: Master you of all people should have confidence in my abilities. I know where my loyalties lie.

Script: OBI-WAN: I hope so . . .
Dialogue: I hope so . . .

Script: ANAKIN: I sense there's more to this talk than you're saying.
Dialogue: I sense there's more to this talk than you're saying.

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin the only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.
Dialogue: Anakin the only reason the Council has approved your appointment is because the Chancellor trusts you.

Script: ANAKIN: And?
Dialogue: And?

Script: OBI-WAN: Anakin look I am on your side. I didn't want to see you put in this situation.
Dialogue: Anakin look I am on your side. I didn't want to see you put in this situation.

Script: ANAKIN: What situation?
Dialogue: What situation?

Script: OBI-WAN: (takes a deep breath) The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.
Dialogue: The Council wants you to report on all of the Chancellor's dealings. They want to know what he's up to.

Script: ANAKIN: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!
Dialogue: They want me to spy on the Chancellor? That's treason!

Script: OBI-WAN: We are at war Anakin. The Jedi Council is sworn to uphold the principles of the Republic even if the Chancellor does not.
Dialogue: We are at war Anakin. The Jedi Council is sworn to uphold the principles of the Republic even if the Chancellor does not.

Script: ANAKIN: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?
Dialogue: Why didn't the Council give me this assignment when we were in session?

Script: OBI-WAN: This assignment is not to be on record. The Council asked me to approach you on this personally.
Dialogue: This assignment is not to be on record. The Council asked me to approach you on this personally.

Script: ANAKIN: The Chancellor is not a bad man Obi-Wan. He befriended me. He's watched out for me ever since I arrived here.
Dialogue: The Chancellor is not a bad man Obi-Wan. He befriended me. He's watched out for me ever since I arrived here.

Script: OBI-WAN: That is why you must help us Anakin. Our allegiance is to the Senate not to its leader who has managed to stay in office long after his term has expired.
Dialogue: That is why you must help us Anakin. Our allegiance is to the Senate not to its leader who has managed to stay in office long after his term has expired.

Script: ANAKIN: Master the Senate demanded that he stay longer.
Dialogue: Master the Senate demanded that he stay longer.

Script: OBI-WAN: Yes but use your feelings Anakin. Something is out of place.
Dialogue: Yes but use your feelings Anakin. Something is out of place.

Script: ANAKIN: You're asking me to do something against the Jedi Code. Against the Republic. Against a mentor . . . and a friend. That's what's out of place here. Why are you asking this of me?
Dialogue: You're asking me to do something against the Jedi Code. Against the Republic. Against a mentor . . . and a friend. That's what's out of place here. Why are you asking this of me?

Script: OBI-WAN: The Council is asking you.
Dialogue: The Council is asking you.

Script: OBI-WAN : Anakin did not take to his assignment with much enthusiasm.
Dialogue: Anakin did not take to his assignment with much enthusiasm.

Script: YODA: Too much under the sway of the Chancellor he is. Much anger there is in him. Too much pride in his powers.
Dialogue: Too much under the sway of the Chancellor he is. Much anger there is in him. Too much pride in his powers.

Script: MACE: It's very dangerous putting them together. I don't think the boy can handle it. I don't trust him.
Dialogue: It's very dangerous putting them together. I don't think the boy can handle it. I don't trust him.

Script: OBI-WAN: He'll be all right. I trust him with my life.
Dialogue: He'll be all right. I trust him with my life.

Script: MACE:I wish I did.
Dialogue: I wish I did.

Script: OBI-WAN: With all due respect Master is he not the Chosen One? Is he not to destroy the Sith and bring balance to the Force?
Dialogue: With all due respect Master is he not the Chosen One? Is he not to destroy the Sith and bring balance to the Force?

Script: MACE: So the prophecy says.
Dialogue: So the prophecy says.

Script: YODA: A prophecy . . . that misread could have been.
Dialogue: A prophecy . . . that misread could have been.

Script: OBI-WAN: He will not let me down. He never has.
Dialogue: He will not let me down. He never has.

Script: YODA: I hope right you are. And now destroy the Droid armies on Kashyyyk I will. May the Force be with you.
Dialogue: I hope right you are. And now destroy the Droid armies on Kashyyyk I will. May the Force be with you.

Script: PADME: Thank you Captain.
Dialogue: Thank you Captain.

Script: CAPTAIN TYPHO: Rest well. My Lady.
Dialogue: Rest well. My Lady.

Script: PADME: I'll be up in a while.
Dialogue: I'll be up in a while.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: MOTEE: Yes my lady.
Dialogue: Yes my lady.

Script: C-3PO: Is there anything I might do for you my lady?
Dialogue: Is there anything I might do for you my lady?

Script: PADME: Yes make sure all the security droids are working. Thank you Threepio.
Dialogue: Yes make sure all the security droids are working. Thank you Threepio.

Script: ANAKIN: Beautiful isn't it?
Dialogue: Beautiful isn't it?

Script: PADME: You startled me.
Dialogue: You startled me.

Script: ANAKIN: How are you feeling?
Dialogue: How are you feeling?

Script: PADME: He keeps kicking.
Dialogue: He keeps kicking.

Script: ANAKIN: He?! Why do you think it's a boy?
Dialogue: He?! Why do you think it's a boy?

Script: PADME: (laughs) My motherly intuition.
Dialogue: My motherly intuition.

Script: ANAKIN: Whoa! With a kick that strong it's got to be a girl.
Dialogue: Whoa! With a kick that strong it's got to be a girl.

Script: PADME: I heard about your appointment. Anakin. I'm so proud of you.
Dialogue: I heard about your appointment. Anakin. I'm so proud of you.

Script: ANAKIN: I may be on the Council but . . . they refused to accept me as a Jedi Master.
Dialogue: I may be on the Council but . . . they refused to accept me as a Jedi Master.

Script: PADME: Patience. In time they will recognize your skills.
Dialogue: Patience. In time they will recognize your skills.

Script: ANAKIN: They still treat me as if I were a Padawan learner. . . they fear my power that's the problem.
Dialogue: They still treat me as if I were a Padawan learner. . . they fear my power that's the problem.

Script: PADME: Anakin . . .
Dialogue: Anakin . . .

Script: ANAKIN: Sometimes I wonder what's happening to the Jedi Order . . . I think this war is destroying the principles of the Republic.
Dialogue: Sometimes I wonder what's happening to the Jedi Order . . . I think this war is destroying the principles of the Republic.

Script: PADME: Have you ever considered that we may be on the wrong side?
Dialogue: Have you ever considered that we may be on the wrong side?

Script: ANAKIN: (suspicious) What do you mean?
Dialogue: What do you mean?

Script: PADME: What if the democracy we thought we were serving no longer exists and the Republic has become the very evil we have been fighting to destroy?
Dialogue: What if the democracy we thought we were serving no longer exists and the Republic has become the very evil we have been fighting to destroy?

Script: ANAKIN: I don't believe that. And you're sounding like a Separatist!
Dialogue: I don't believe that. And you're sounding like a Separatist!

Script: PADME: Anakin this war represents a failure to listen . . . Now you're closer to the Chancellor than anyone. Please please ask him to stop the fighting and let diplomacy resume.
Dialogue: Anakin this war represents a failure to listen . . . Now you're closer to the Chancellor than anyone. Please please ask him to stop the fighting and let diplomacy resume.

Script: ANAKIN: (growing angry) Don't ask me to do that Padme. Make a motion in the Senate where that kind of a request belongs. I'm not your errand boy. I'm not anyone's errand boy!
Dialogue: Don't ask me to do that Padme. Make a motion in the Senate where that kind of a request belongs. I'm not your errand boy. I'm not anyone's errand boy!

Script: PADME: What is it?
Dialogue: What is it?

Script: ANAKIN: Nothing.
Dialogue: Nothing.

Script: PADME: Don't do this . . . don't shut me out. Let me help you.
Dialogue: Don't do this . . . don't shut me out. Let me help you.

Script: ANAKIN: You can't help me . . . I'm trying to help you.
Dialogue: You can't help me . . . I'm trying to help you.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) I sense . . . there are things you are not telling me.
Dialogue: I sense . . . there are things you are not telling me.

Script: PADME: I sense there are things you are not telling me.
Dialogue: I sense there are things you are not telling me.

Script: PADME: (continuing) Hold me . . . like you did by the lake on Naboo so long ago . . . when there was nothing but our love ... No politics no plotting ... no war.
Dialogue: Hold me . . . like you did by the lake on Naboo so long ago . . . when there was nothing but our love ... No politics no plotting ... no war.

Script: ANAKIN: You wanted to see me Chancellor.
Dialogue: You wanted to see me Chancellor.

Script: PALPATINE: Yes Anakin! Come closer. I have good news. Our Clone Intelligence Units have discovered the location of General Grievous. He is hiding in the Utapau system.
Dialogue: Yes Anakin! Come closer. I have good news. Our Clone Intelligence Units have discovered the location of General Grievous. He is hiding in the Utapau system.

Script: ANAKIN: At last we'll be able to capture that monster and end this war.
Dialogue: At last we'll be able to capture that monster and end this war.

Script: PALPATINE: I would worry about the collective wisdom of the Council if they didn't select you for this assignment. You are the best choice by far  but they can't always be trusted to do the right thing.
Dialogue: I would worry about the collective wisdom of the Council if they didn't select you for this assignment. You are the best choice by far  but they can't always be trusted to do the right thing.

Script: ANAKIN: They try.
Dialogue: They try.

Script: PALPATINE: Sit down (to his aides) Leave us.
Dialogue: Sit down  Leave us.

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) Anakin you know I'm not able to rely on the Jedi Council. If they haven't included you in their plot they soon will.
Dialogue: Anakin you know I'm not able to rely on the Jedi Council. If they haven't included you in their plot they soon will.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm not sure I understand.
Dialogue: I'm not sure I understand.

Script: PALPATINE: You must sense what I have come to suspect . . . the Jedi Council want control of the Republic . . . they're planning to betray me.
Dialogue: You must sense what I have come to suspect . . . the Jedi Council want control of the Republic . . . they're planning to betray me.

Script: ANAKIN: I don't think . . .
Dialogue: I don't think . . .

Script: PALPATINE: Anakin search your feelings. You know don't you?
Dialogue: Anakin search your feelings. You know don't you?

Script: ANAKIN: I know they don't trust you . . .
Dialogue: I know they don't trust you . . .

Script: PALPATINE: Or the Senate . . . or the Republic . . . or democracy for that matter.
Dialogue: Or the Senate . . . or the Republic . . . or democracy for that matter.

Script: ANAKIN: I have to admit my trust in them has been shaken.
Dialogue: I have to admit my trust in them has been shaken.

Script: PALPATINE: Why? They asked you to do something that made you feel dishonest didn't they?
Dialogue: Why? They asked you to do something that made you feel dishonest didn't they?

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) They asked you to spy on me didn't they?
Dialogue: They asked you to spy on me didn't they?

Script: ANAKIN: I don't know ... I don't know what to say.
Dialogue: I don't know ... I don't know what to say.

Script: PALPATINE: Remember back to your early teachings. Anakin. "All those who gain power are afraid to lose it." Even the Jedi.
Dialogue: Remember back to your early teachings. Anakin. "All those who gain power are afraid to lose it." Even the Jedi.

Script: ANAKIN: The Jedi use their power for good.
Dialogue: The Jedi use their power for good.

Script: PALPATINE: Good is a point of view Anakin. And the Jedi point of view is not the only valid one. The Dark Lords of the Sith believe in security and justice also yet they are considered by the Jedi to be. . .
Dialogue: Good is a point of view Anakin. And the Jedi point of view is not the only valid one. The Dark Lords of the Sith believe in security and justice also yet they are considered by the Jedi to be. . .

Script: ANAKIN: . . . evil.
Dialogue: . . . evil.

Script: PALPATINE: . . . from a Jedi's point of view. The Sith and the Jedi are similar in almost every way including their quest for greater power. The difference between the two is the Sith are not afraid of the dark side of the Force. That is why they are more powerful.
Dialogue: . . . from a Jedi's point of view. The Sith and the Jedi are similar in almost every way including their quest for greater power. The difference between the two is the Sith are not afraid of the dark side of the Force. That is why they are more powerful.

Script: ANAKIN: The Sith rely on their passion for their strength. They think inward only about themselves.
Dialogue: The Sith rely on their passion for their strength. They think inward only about themselves.

Script: PALPATINE: And the Jedi don't?
Dialogue: And the Jedi don't?

Script: ANAKIN: The Jedi are selfless . . . they only care about others.
Dialogue: The Jedi are selfless . . . they only care about others.

Script: PALPATINE: Or so you've been trained to believe. Why is it then that they have asked you to do something you feel is wrong?
Dialogue: Or so you've been trained to believe. Why is it then that they have asked you to do something you feel is wrong?

Script: ANAKIN: I'm not sure it's wrong.
Dialogue: I'm not sure it's wrong.

Script: PALPATINE: Have they asked you to betray the Jedi code? The Constitution? A friendship? Your own values? Think. Consider their motives. Keep your mind clear of assumptions. The fear of losing power is a weakness of both the Jedi and the Sith.
Dialogue: Have they asked you to betray the Jedi code? The Constitution? A friendship? Your own values? Think. Consider their motives. Keep your mind clear of assumptions. The fear of losing power is a weakness of both the Jedi and the Sith.

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) Did you ever hear the tragedy of Darth Plagueis "the wise"?
Dialogue: Did you ever hear the tragedy of Darth Plagueis "the wise"?

Script: ANAKIN: No.
Dialogue: No.

Script: PALPATINE: I thought not. It's not a story the Jedi would tell you. It's a Sith legend. Darth Plagueis was a Dark Lord of the Sith so powerful and so wise he could use the Force to influence the midi-chlorians to create life ... He had such a knowledge of the dark side that he could even keep the ones he cared about from dying.
Dialogue: I thought not. It's not a story the Jedi would tell you. It's a Sith legend. Darth Plagueis was a Dark Lord of the Sith so powerful and so wise he could use the Force to influence the midi-chlorians to create life ... He had such a knowledge of the dark side that he could even keep the ones he cared about from dying.

Script: ANAKIN: He could actually save people from death?
Dialogue: He could actually save people from death?

Script: PALPATINE: The dark side of the Force is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural.
Dialogue: The dark side of the Force is a pathway to many abilities some consider to be unnatural.

Script: ANAKIN: What happened to him?
Dialogue: What happened to him?

Script: PALPATINE: He became so powerful . . . the only thing he was afraid of was losing his power which eventually of course he did. Unfortunately he taught his apprentice everything he knew then his apprentice killed him in his sleep. (smiles) Plagueis never saw it coming. It's ironic he could save others from death but not himself.
Dialogue: He became so powerful . . . the only thing he was afraid of was losing his power which eventually of course he did. Unfortunately he taught his apprentice everything he knew then his apprentice killed him in his sleep.  Plagueis never saw it coming. It's ironic he could save others from death but not himself.

Script: ANAKIN: Is it possible to learn this power?
Dialogue: Is it possible to learn this power?

Script: PALPATINE: Not from a Jedi.
Dialogue: Not from a Jedi.

Script: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: (holo) Palpatine thinks General Grievous is on Utapau. We have had no reports of this from our agents.
Dialogue: Palpatine thinks General Grievous is on Utapau. We have had no reports of this from our agents.

Script: MACE: (holo) How could the Chancellor have come by this information and we know nothing about it? We have had contact with Baron Papanoida and he said no one was there.
Dialogue: How could the Chancellor have come by this information and we know nothing about it? We have had contact with Baron Papanoida and he said no one was there.

Script: ANAKIN: A partial message was intercepted in a diplomatic packet from the Chairman of Utapau.
Dialogue: A partial message was intercepted in a diplomatic packet from the Chairman of Utapau.

Script: YODA: Act on this we must. The capture of General Grievous will end this war. Quickly and decisively we should proceed.
Dialogue: Act on this we must. The capture of General Grievous will end this war. Quickly and decisively we should proceed.

Script: OBI-WAN: Does everyone agree?
Dialogue: Does everyone agree?

Script: ANAKIN: The Chancellor has requested that I lead the campaign.
Dialogue: The Chancellor has requested that I lead the campaign.

Script: MACE: (a little peeved) The Council will make up its own mind who is to go not the Chancellor.
Dialogue: The Council will make up its own mind who is to go not the Chancellor.

Script: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: Yes this decision is ours to make.
Dialogue: Yes this decision is ours to make.

Script: YODA: A Master is needed with more experience.
Dialogue: A Master is needed with more experience.

Script: MACE: Given our resources I recommend we send only one Jedi . . . Master Kenobi.
Dialogue: Given our resources I recommend we send only one Jedi . . . Master Kenobi.

Script: ANAKIN: He was not so successful the last time he met Grievous.
Dialogue: He was not so successful the last time he met Grievous.

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) No offense my Master but I'm only stating a fact.
Dialogue: No offense my Master but I'm only stating a fact.

Script: OBI-WAN: Oh no you're quite right but I do have the most experience with his ways of combat.
Dialogue: Oh no you're quite right but I do have the most experience with his ways of combat.

Script: YODA: Obi-Wan my choice is.
Dialogue: Obi-Wan my choice is.

Script: Kl-ADI-MUNDI: I concur. Master Kenobi should go.
Dialogue: I concur. Master Kenobi should go.

Script: YODA: I agree.
Dialogue: I agree.

Script: MACE: Very well. Council is adjourned.
Dialogue: Very well. Council is adjourned.

Script: MACE: (continuing) Obi-Wan prepare two clone brigades as quickly as you can. If this report is true there's no telling how many battle droids he may have with him.
Dialogue: Obi-Wan prepare two clone brigades as quickly as you can. If this report is true there's no telling how many battle droids he may have with him.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER GREE: The droids have started up their main power generators.
Dialogue: The droids have started up their main power generators.

Script: YODA: Then now the time is Commander.
Dialogue: Then now the time is Commander.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER GREE: Yes sir.
Dialogue: Yes sir.

Script: OBI-WAN: Has Anakin been to see you?
Dialogue: Has Anakin been to see you?

Script: PADME: Several times . . . I was so happy to hear he was accepted on the Jedi Council.
Dialogue: Several times . . . I was so happy to hear he was accepted on the Jedi Council.

Script: OBI-WAN: I know ... he deserves it. He is impatient strong willed very opinionated but truly gifted.
Dialogue: I know ... he deserves it. He is impatient strong willed very opinionated but truly gifted.

Script: PADME: You're not just here to say hello. Something is wrong isn't it?
Dialogue: You're not just here to say hello. Something is wrong isn't it?

Script: OBI-WAN: You should be a Jedi Padme.
Dialogue: You should be a Jedi Padme.

Script: PADME: You're not very good at hiding your feelings.
Dialogue: You're not very good at hiding your feelings.

Script: OBI-WAN: It's Anakin . . . He's becoming moody and detached. He's been put in a difficult position as the Chancellor's representative . . . but I think it's more than that. I was hoping he may have talked to you.
Dialogue: It's Anakin . . . He's becoming moody and detached. He's been put in a difficult position as the Chancellor's representative . . . but I think it's more than that. I was hoping he may have talked to you.

Script: PADME: Why would he talk to me about his work?
Dialogue: Why would he talk to me about his work?

Script: OBI-WAN: Neither of you is very good at hiding your feelings either.
Dialogue: Neither of you is very good at hiding your feelings either.

Script: PADME: Don't give me that look.
Dialogue: Don't give me that look.

Script: OBI-WAN: I know how he feels about you.
Dialogue: I know how he feels about you.

Script: PADME: (nervous) What did he say?
Dialogue: What did he say?

Script: OBI-WAN: Nothing. He didn't have to.
Dialogue: Nothing. He didn't have to.

Script: PADME: I don't know what you're talking about.
Dialogue: I don't know what you're talking about.

Script: OBI-WAN: I know you both too well. I can see you two are in love. Padme I'm worried about him.
Dialogue: I know you both too well. I can see you two are in love. Padme I'm worried about him.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) I fear your relationship has confused him. He's changed considerably since we returned . . .
Dialogue: I fear your relationship has confused him. He's changed considerably since we returned . . .

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) Padme I'm not telling the Council about any of this. I ... I hope I didn't upset you. We're all friends I care about both of you . . .
Dialogue: Padme I'm not telling the Council about any of this. I ... I hope I didn't upset you. We're all friends I care about both of you . . .

Script: PADME: Thank you Obi-Wan.
Dialogue: Thank you Obi-Wan.

Script: OBI-WAN: Please do what you can to help him.
Dialogue: Please do what you can to help him.

Script: PADME: We cannot let this turn into another war.
Dialogue: We cannot let this turn into another war.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Absolutely that is the last thing we want.
Dialogue: Absolutely that is the last thing we want.

Script: MON MOTHMA: We are hoping to form an alliance in the Senate to stop the Chancellor from further subverting the constitution that's all.
Dialogue: We are hoping to form an alliance in the Senate to stop the Chancellor from further subverting the constitution that's all.

Script: PADME: I know a Jedi I feel it would be wise to consult.
Dialogue: I know a Jedi I feel it would be wise to consult.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: BANA BREEMU: That would be dangerous.
Dialogue: That would be dangerous.

Script: MON MOTHMA: We don't know where the Jedi stand in all this.
Dialogue: We don't know where the Jedi stand in all this.

Script: PADME: I only wish to discuss this with one . . . one I trust.
Dialogue: I only wish to discuss this with one . . . one I trust.

Script: GiDDEAN DANU: Going against the Chancellor without the support of the Jedi is risky.
Dialogue: Going against the Chancellor without the support of the Jedi is risky.

Script: PADME: The Jedi aren't any happier with the situation than we are . . .
Dialogue: The Jedi aren't any happier with the situation than we are . . .

Script: CHI EEKWAY: Patience Senator.
Dialogue: Patience Senator.

Script: FANG ZAR: We have so many Senators on our side surely that will pursuade the Chancellor.
Dialogue: We have so many Senators on our side surely that will pursuade the Chancellor.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BANA BREEMU: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.
Dialogue: When you present the "petition of the two thousand" to the Chancellor things may change.

Script: BAIL ORGANA: Let us see what we can accomplish in the Senate before we include the Jedi.
Dialogue: Let us see what we can accomplish in the Senate before we include the Jedi.

Script: ANAKIN: You're going to need me on this one Master.
Dialogue: You're going to need me on this one Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: Oh I agree. However it may turn out just to be a wild bantha chase.
Dialogue: Oh I agree. However it may turn out just to be a wild bantha chase.

Script: ANAKIN: Master!
Dialogue: Master!

Script: ANAKIN: (continuing) Master I've disappointed you. I have not been very appreciative of your training . . . I have been arrogant and I apologize . . . I've just been so frustrated with the Council. Your friendship means everything to me.
Dialogue: Master I've disappointed you. I have not been very appreciative of your training . . . I have been arrogant and I apologize . . . I've just been so frustrated with the Council. Your friendship means everything to me.

Script: OBI-WAN: You are strong and wise Anakin and I am very proud of you. I have trained you since you were a small boy. I have taught you everything I know. And you have become a far greater Jedi than I could ever hope to be and you have saved my life more times than I can remember. But be patient Anakin. It won't be long before the Council makes you a Jedi Master.
Dialogue: You are strong and wise Anakin and I am very proud of you. I have trained you since you were a small boy. I have taught you everything I know. And you have become a far greater Jedi than I could ever hope to be and you have saved my life more times than I can remember. But be patient Anakin. It won't be long before the Council makes you a Jedi Master.

Script: OBI-WAN: (continuing) Don't worry. I have enough clones with me to take three systems the size of Utapau. I think I'll be able to handle the situation . . . even without your help.
Dialogue: Don't worry. I have enough clones with me to take three systems the size of Utapau. I think I'll be able to handle the situation . . . even without your help.

Script: ANAKIN: Well there's always a first time.
Dialogue: Well there's always a first time.

Script: ANAKIN: Obi-Wan may the Force be with you.
Dialogue: Obi-Wan may the Force be with you.

Script: OBI-WAN: Good-bye old friend. May the Force be with you.
Dialogue: Good-bye old friend. May the Force be with you.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: Fortunately most of the cities are concentrated on this small continent here . . . on the far side.
Dialogue: Fortunately most of the cities are concentrated on this small continent here . . . on the far side.

Script: OBI-WAN: I'll keep them distracted until you get there. Just don't take too long.
Dialogue: I'll keep them distracted until you get there. Just don't take too long.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: Come on boss when have I ever let you down?
Dialogue: Come on boss when have I ever let you down?

Script: OBI-WAN: (laughing) Cato Nemoidia . . . for starters.
Dialogue: Cato Nemoidia . . . for starters.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: That was Anakin who was late. I believe.
Dialogue: That was Anakin who was late. I believe.

Script: OBI-WAN: Very well the burden is on me not to destroy all the droids before you get there.
Dialogue: Very well the burden is on me not to destroy all the droids before you get there.

Script: CLONE COMMANDER CODY: I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: I'm counting on you.

Script: PALPATINE: Well Anakin did you see your friend off?
Dialogue: Well Anakin did you see your friend off?

Script: ANAKIN: He will soon have Grievous's head.
Dialogue: He will soon have Grievous's head.

Script: PALPATINE: We can only hope the Council didn't make a mistake.
Dialogue: We can only hope the Council didn't make a mistake.

Script: ANAKIN: The Council was very sure in its decision.
Dialogue: The Council was very sure in its decision.

Script: JAR JAR: Helloo Annie. Good en to see yousa . . .
Dialogue: Helloo Annie. Good en to see yousa . . .

Script: ANAKIN: Hi Jar Jar.
Dialogue: Hi Jar Jar.

Script: JAR JAR: Oopsin da Chancellor!! So sorry Your Highness sir.
Dialogue: Oopsin da Chancellor!! So sorry Your Highness sir.

Script: PALPATINE: There are rumors in the Senate about Master Kenobi. Many believe he is not fit for this assignment.
Dialogue: There are rumors in the Senate about Master Kenobi. Many believe he is not fit for this assignment.

Script: ANAKIN: Not fit? Why would anyone think that?
Dialogue: Not fit? Why would anyone think that?

Script: PALPATINE: They say his mind has become fogged by the influence of a certain female Senator.
Dialogue: They say his mind has become fogged by the influence of a certain female Senator.

Script: ANAKIN: That's ridiculous. Who?!?
Dialogue: That's ridiculous. Who?!?

Script: PALPATINE: (slyly) No one knows who she is ... only that she is a Senator.
Dialogue: No one knows who she is ... only that she is a Senator.

Script: ANAKIN: That's impossible. I would know.
Dialogue: That's impossible. I would know.

Script: PALPATINE: Sometimes the closest are the ones who cannot see.
Dialogue: Sometimes the closest are the ones who cannot see.

Script: PALPATINE: (continuing) Idle Senate gossip is rarely true and never accurate. I'm sure your Master will do fine.
Dialogue: Idle Senate gossip is rarely true and never accurate. I'm sure your Master will do fine.

Script: OBI-WAN: Save your energy.
Dialogue: Save your energy.

Script: PADME: I can't!
Dialogue: I can't!

Script: OBI-WAN: Don't give up Padme. Don't give up . . .
Dialogue: Don't give up Padme. Don't give up . . .

Script: ANAKIN: I sense someone familiar . . . Obi-Wan's been here hasn't he?
Dialogue: I sense someone familiar . . . Obi-Wan's been here hasn't he?

Script: PADME: He came by this morning.
Dialogue: He came by this morning.

Script: ANAKIN: What did he want?
Dialogue: What did he want?

Script: PADME: He's worried about you.
Dialogue: He's worried about you.

Script: ANAKIN: You told him about us didn't you?
Dialogue: You told him about us didn't you?

Script: PADME: He's your best friend Anakin. He says you're under a lot of stress.
Dialogue: He's your best friend Anakin. He says you're under a lot of stress.

Script: ANAKIN: And he's not?
Dialogue: And he's not?

Script: PADME: You have been moody lately.
Dialogue: You have been moody lately.

Script: ANAKIN: I'm not moody . . .
Dialogue: I'm not moody . . .

Script: PADME: Anakin! Don't do this again.
Dialogue: Anakin! Don't do this again.

Script: ANAKIN: I don't know ... I feel . . . lost.
Dialogue: I don't know ... I feel . . . lost.

Script: PADME: Lost? What do you mean? You're always so sure of yourself. I don't understand.
Dialogue: Lost? What do you mean? You're always so sure of yourself. I don't understand.

Script: ANAKIN: Obi-Wan and the Council don't trust me.
Dialogue: Obi-Wan and the Council don't trust me.

Script: PADME: They trust you with their lives. Obi-Wan loves you as a son.
Dialogue: They trust you with their lives. Obi-Wan loves you as a son.

Script: ANAKIN: Something's happening . . . I'm not the Jedi I should be. I am one of the most powerful Jedi but I'm not satisfied ... I want more and I know I shouldn't.
Dialogue: Something's happening . . . I'm not the Jedi I should be. I am one of the most powerful Jedi but I'm not satisfied ... I want more and I know I shouldn't.

Script: PADME: You expect too much of yourself.
Dialogue: You expect too much of yourself.

Script: ANAKIN: I have found a way to save you.
Dialogue: I have found a way to save you.

Script: PADME: Save me?
Dialogue: Save me?

Script: ANAKIN: From my nightmares.
Dialogue: From my nightmares.

Script: PADME: Is that what's bothering you?
Dialogue: Is that what's bothering you?

Script: ANAKIN: I won't lose you Padme.
Dialogue: I won't lose you Padme.

Script: PADME: I'm not going to die in childbirth Annie. I promise you.
Dialogue: I'm not going to die in childbirth Annie. I promise you.

Script: ANAKIN: No I promise you! I am becoming so powerful with my new knowledge of the Force I will be able to keep you from dying.
Dialogue: No I promise you! I am becoming so powerful with my new knowledge of the Force I will be able to keep you from dying.

Script: PADME: You don't need more power Anakin. I believe you can protect me against anything just as you are.
Dialogue: You don't need more power Anakin. I believe you can protect me against anything just as you are.

Script: TlON MEDON: Greetings young Jedi. What brings you to our remote sanctuary?
Dialogue: Greetings young Jedi. What brings you to our remote sanctuary?

Script: OBI-WAN: Unfortunately the war.
Dialogue: Unfortunately the war.
